title: banana pineapple pie
directions: At room temperature, mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy. Pour into pie crusts.
Layer pineapple and then bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: southern style stuffed yams(a southern style favorite)
directions: Heat
oven
Bake yams until tender, approximately 1 hour.
Cool slightly.
Slice yams lengthwise.
Scoop out	pulp, leaving a shell of potato pulp to protect the thin skin
of
the yams.
Combine peanut butter, milk, cinnamon and allspice
with the scooped-out pulp while still warm, and mash thoroughly.
Fill hollowed-out potato skins with the mixture, mounding
slightly. Mix
the
peanuts
and
bread
crumbs and scatter
evenly
over tops
of
stuffed yams.
Drizzle melted butter
evenly
over
all, and
place under broiler to brown. Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Break bread into pieces the size of a quarter and break cheese into bite-size pieces.
Arrange shrimp, bread and cheese in layers in a greased casserole and pour melted butter over all.
Beat eggs.
Add mustard and salt, then add milk.
Pour over casserole. Stand a minimum of 3 hours or preferably overnight, covered.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
To double, use 3 pounds shrimp.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 11 x 16 pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion seasoned with garlic salt and oregano.
Drain well.
Combine meat, sauce and Ricotta cheese. Save a little sauce to cover bottom of baking dish.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain well.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Combine sausage, eggs and cheese.
Add raw eggs and evaporated milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, cream cheese and ice cream until smooth. Add other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: ho-bo's
directions: Make patties out of hamburger meat.
Slice potatoes, onions and carrots, thin.
Place onion slice on Reynolds Wrap large enough to wrap Ho-bo in.
Place hamburger pattie on top of onion, add sliced potatoes and carrots.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap in Reynolds Wrap.
Place each Ho-bo on a pan and bake at 375° until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix and put in baking dish. Crunch potato chips on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pulliam pie-casserole dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine soups, green enchilada sauce, and green chilies into hamburger meat that has been drained.
Place in layers, broken tortillas, then hamburger mixture, then cheese. Repeat.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: knox blox
directions: Pour water over gelatin and jello, stirring well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator until set.
Cut in squares or other choice of design.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all 6 ingredients in ungreased rectangular baking dish.
Then mix baking mix and milk.
Pour over evenly the soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet kosher dill pickles
directions: Pour liquid off the pickles.
Add 1/2 inch water, sugar and vinegar.
Put on cover and roll until the sugar doesn't settle. Turn jar on its top and alternate it twice a day from top to bottom for 4 days.
Refrigerate when done.

title: heart tarts
directions: Put the peanut butter in a big bowl.
Pour in the honey and mix with a spoon.
Add the dry milk.
Mix everything together with your hands until you have a soft smooth ball of dough.
Roll pieces of dough on a wood board into a ball about the size of a marble.
Press the ball to make a round cookie.
Make cookie into heart shape.
Put a dab of jam in the middle of each heart.
Put the hearts on a plate.
Keep them in the refrigerator for 1 hour or more.
Makes 30 hearts.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first seven ingredients and shape into small balls.
Brown in skillet.
Pour off drippings and stir in soup and water.
Cover and cook on low heat for 20 minutes.
Stir often.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream the sour cream and cream cheese in mixer bowl until smooth.
Add salad dressing mix and lemon juice; mix well.
Fold in shrimp.
Chill, covered, for 1 hour or longer.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Mix with melted butter. Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Beat eggs, 2 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Add 1/4 cup flour and brown sugar to mixture.
Pour over crust.
Bake an additional 25 minutes.
Cool on rack and sprinkle with powdered sugar, just before serving.

title: frosty mandarin jello salad
directions: Drain
oranges,
measuring syrup. Add water to syrup to make 1
cup. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.	Add measured liquid. Add
sherbet
by
spoonfuls,
stirring
until melted. Chill
until thickened.
Fold in oranges, reserving a few for garnish.	Pour into a
serving
bowl.
Chill until set.
Makes about 5 cups or 8 servings.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into loaf pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: grandma's marble cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan (do not flour).
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks, beaten well.
Sift salt, baking powder and flour.
Add to first mixture, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Divide batter into 2 parts.
Add chocolate to one.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Divide it in half, fold each half into each half of batter (1/2 in chocolate and 1/2 in vanilla).
Put one spoonful of vanilla and one of chocolate alternating until you fill the pan.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 45 minutes).

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill milk until icy cold.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Chill until partially set.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Whip chilled milk and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Line bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of crumbs.
Pour gelatin mixture into pan and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and top each with a cherry.

title: aunt mag's caramel pie
directions: Brown
sugar
and
flour in heavy iron skillet over low heat until it browns, stirring all the time.
Add the milk and stir until
thick
and all melted.
Add butter and cool.
Beat the egg yolks
until
they	are light and add while stirring. Add vanilla. When cool, stack between three cooked pie crusts like
cake filling.
Beat
egg
whites
until	stiff.	Add
8 teaspoons sugar,
one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Put on top and brown.
The crusts have no sides, just roll out 9 inches round and bake.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: In a large mixer bowl, cream the butter at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add sugar.
Continue creaming at high speed until light and fluffy. No need to sift flour, measure by lightly spooning into a cup and leveling off.
By hand, stir in flour, dry frosting mix and walnuts until well blended.
Pour batter into a greased Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours.

title: stromboli
directions: Spread 1 loaf of frozen (thawed) bread dough on a cookie sheet. Lengthwise in the center, make 2 rows of pepperoni.
Sprinkle mozzarella cheese over the pepperoni.
Lay thin ham strips over the cheese.
Put shredded cheddar cheese over ham.
Fold each side over the middle and crimp edges and ends.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: golden punch
directions: *If mashed in blender, add 1/2 cup water.

title: one minute caramel icing
directions: Put 1/2 cup sugar in black skillet and heat until it melts. Heat 1 1/2 cups sugar, butter and milk.
When hot, add the sugar you have melted and cook for 1 minute after it begins to boil. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth enough to go on cool cake.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Mix altogether and dot Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake at 350°.

title: arizona salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350°.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Mix shortening, butter, brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Cook slowly for three minutes.
Add powdered sugar and beat until consistency is equal to spread.

title: jello salad
directions: Melt jello in hot water.
Add strawberries (while frozen) to jello and water.
Add mashed bananas and crushed pineapple.
Place half of jello mixture in dish and let set.
Combine sour cream and cream cheese.
Add cream mixture over set jello and rest of jello mixture on top.
Cool for a few hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon mixture into hot fat and fry until brown.

title: chicken liver with bacon and green beans
directions: Trim livers.
Cook bacon.
Crumble.
Drain on paper towels. Reserve 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings in a large skillet.
Roll chicken livers in flour to coat.
Brown on all sides in drippings (5 to 10 minutes).
Stir in 1/4 cup water, scraping up brown bits from skillet.
Add beans.
Cover and cook 10 minutes, until beans are tender.
Livers should be brown outside and slightly pink inside.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Serve on white rice or with fried rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pot roast
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over roast and bake (covered tightly) at 225° for 4 to 6 hours.
Makes a delicious gravy which can be thickened with a little cornstarch dissolved in cold water.

title: fruited ham dinner
directions: Combine fruit and pumpkin spice.
Pour off 1/2 cup syrup. Heat oven to 350°.
Place ham in oblong baking dish.
Arrange sweet potatoes around ham.
Mix brown sugar, reserved fruit syrup and dry mustard.
Pour over ham and potatoes.
Bake 1 hour, basting ham and potatoes every 15 minutes.
Drain fruit and arrange across top and sides.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes.

title: stir-fry beef with broccoli and mushrooms
directions: Mix soy sauce, vinegar and sugar in a small bowl; set aside. In another bowl, mix bouillon cube, water and cornstarch. Assemble remaining ingredients to cook.

In a wok, heat 1 1/2 tablespoons oil over high heat. Add garlic and cook a few seconds to season oil. Add meat; stir-fry 2 minutes until slices are brown outside but still pink inside. Remove meat and juices from pan to bowl. Discard garlic.
Wipe out wok.
Add 1/2 tablespoon oil around pan edge.
Add broccoli florets and mushrooms. Stir-fry 2 minutes. Add meat and juices
to vegetables, then soy mixture. Stir, cover and cook 2 minutes. Stir cornstarch mixture and pour into wok with vegetables and meat.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 to 3 minutes until thick.

title: scalloped yams and apples
directions: Arrange half the yams, cut side down, in shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Add half the apples.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle half on mixture.
Repeat layers.
Cover with lid or foil and bake at 350° until apples are tender, about an hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and oats and mix well. Press firmly and evenly into lightly buttered cookie sheet (approximately 10 x 14-inch).
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Cut into squares immediately then cool in pan.

title: brandied apples(serves 7)
directions: Peel and core apples.
Leave apples whole.
Let water and sugar mixture come to a boil.
Drop apples in mixture and add lemon juice.
Cook on medium-high until tender.
Don't stir or burn.
Remove from heat.
Pour into a casserole type baking dish. Add cherries.
Bake in 375° oven until syrup boils up.
Remove from oven and immediately add 1/2 cup bourbon or brandy.
Light and serve.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Mix together soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over carrots, pepper and onion in an airtight container.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: egg custard
directions: This recipe makes 2 custards.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, melted oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan or baking dish. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: sloppy joe pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef and onion, drain, and mix ketchup, brown sugar, and cook for 10 minutes.
Spread into 9 inch pie plate; sprinkle with cheese.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour on top of cheese.
Bake 25 minutes.
Serves 4-5.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter with brown sugar and salt over medium flame; add milk and bring to a boil.
Remove from fire and add confectioners sugar.
Stir until blended or mix with electric beater until smooth.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, add beef and mix well.
Shape into six patties: 3/4 in. thick.
Broil 3 ins. from heat for 6 mins.
Turn and broil 4 mins. longer.

title: children's party punch
directions: Turn lemonade into punch bowl.
Add 1 pint ice cream, beat until smooth.
Tint milk with food coloring.
Stir into lemonade mixture.
Scoop remaining ice cream into punch.
Yields 12 servings.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes, cool, dice, set aside.
Fry, drain well and chop bacon, set aside. Chop onions including tops, set aside. Melt margarine on low heat in large sauce pan.
Add flour stirring constantly for one minute.
Gradually add milk and cook until thick and bubbly.
Add diced potatoes, salt, pepper, 2 Tbsp chopped onion, 1/2 cup bacon, and 1 cup of cheese.

title: vidalia onion casserole(given out by the vidalia onion association)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray large casserole dish with Pam. Slice onions and make into rings.
Spread one layer in bottom of dish until covered.
Spread Ritz crackers over onion layer.
Brown sausage and drain.
Spread over Ritz crackers.
Layer remaining onions over sausage until covered completely.
Spread one can of mushroom soup over onion layer.
Spread Cheddar cheese over soup and sprinkle pimentos over top for color.
Bake in covered dish for 1 hour.

title: quick-baked pasta
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil. Heat a large frying pan and add the oil, beef and garlic. Saute until the meat is tender, then drain off the excess fat. Add all remaining ingredients, except the cheese for the topping and the pasta. Simmer the mixture while the pasta cooks until tender. Drain the pasta and mix it with the sauce. Pour all into a 3-quart glass rectangular baking dish with the remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until all is bubbly hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: To sugar, mix melted margarine and remaining ingredients. Pour into pie shells; bake 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: marinated green pea salad
directions: Bring to a boil and boil for one minute: sugar, vinegar, water, salt and white pepper.
Cool completely.
Combine vegetables and pour marinade over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate nutty delight
directions: Mix flour, butter, and pecans together for crust, bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until light brown. Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, and cool whip. Mix well and spread over crust. Mix well chocolate pudding and milk and spread over the first mixture. Spread remaining cool whip over top of the chocolate mixture and chill over night.

title: mexican fried rice
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, heat oil and add rice.
Cook until golden brown, stirring often.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring mixture to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Season to taste.
Serve with additional salsa, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: raisin crunch granola bars
directions: Mix all ingredients with 6 to 8 drops of water to get workable consistency.
Press into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into 8 equal slices. Serves 8.

title: goodie bars
directions: Bake at 350° for 8 minutes in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pat on bottom good.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spread evenly in an 8 or 10-inch pie plate.
Cover with chili sauce and crabmeat.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with dried parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut off and discard tips of wings.
Mix all of the ingredients together and pour over wings in a large shallow dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Mix water with cornstarch.
Stir into hot mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Cool.
Spoon over cheesecake, cottage pudding or gingerbread.

title: never fail sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks 5 minutes.
Add water and sugar, beating 4 minutes.
Sift together flour and salt; stir into yolks.
Beat egg whites frothy, add cream of tartar and beat until they hold peaks.
Fold into yolk mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in tube pan.

title: bread pudding with bourbon sauce
directions: Pour milk over bread and soak about 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Whisk together sugar, eggs, vanilla, nutmeg and raisins. Combine bread and sugar mixture.
Smooth into 9 x 13-inch glass pan that has been buttered.
Bake about 1 hour or until done in center.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat eggs, bread, catsup, water and soup thoroughly.
Put into pan.
Cover with 2 strips bacon.
Pour the tomato sauce over all.
Bake 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put
in
an 8 x 8-inch baking dish the sweet potatoes, sugar, 1/2 cup butter, eggs, vanilla and milk. Mix together and put on top brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup butter and nuts.
Bake at 350°for 25 minutes.

title: english muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cool to lukewarm by adding 1/2 cup water.
Add yeast.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Mix to soft dough.

title: key lime pie
directions: With mixer combine juice and milk; add food dye.
Slowly add Cool Whip and blend thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill several hours.
Serve chilled.

title: peel-a-pound soup
directions: Chop vegetables.
Put in large pot and cover with water. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add soup mix.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Line 10 x 14-inch pan with the bread.
Layer the chicken over the bread and add a layer of the mushrooms and water chestnuts. Dot with the green pepper.
Spread the soup over the top of this. Add the pimento and lay the cheese over the top.
Beat the eggs, add the milk and salt and pour over all.

title: chicken and black bean chili
directions: In large skillet with nonstick cooking spray, brown chicken and onion over medium heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce to low; simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: roast with gravy
directions: Flour and brown meat in small amount of cooking oil.
Salt a little.
Mix onion soup mix with mushroom soup and 2 cans of water.
Cook, covered, 3 to 4 hours (may be 5 if you want it real tender) at 325°.
Check water level after 3 hours.
Add more, if needed.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unfold dinner rolls and fit to cover a large ungreased cookie sheet, overlapping and sealing the edges to make 1 large square. Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients. Spread on cooled crust.
Top with finely chopped vegetables, about 3 cups:
carrots, radishes, peppers, cauliflower or any veggie that is colorful.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute onions.
Cook noodles and drain well.
Mix soups, sour cream, corn and pimentos in large bowl.
Add beef, onion and noodles; mix well.
Place in 3-quart casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and place around a 16-inch pizza pan.
Bake as directed on package.
Cool.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in a large microwave bowl on High 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through. Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Stir in vanilla and walnuts. Spread in a greased 8-inch square pan. Refrigerate until firm. Cut into squares.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lemon punch
directions: Mix jello in hot water. Add sugar and cold water. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Then add pineapple juice, lemon juice and almond extract. Freeze in 3 half-gallon milk cartons and take out of freezer 2 hours before serving. Add ginger ale and serve. Will serve about 50.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Mix soft butter, sugar and pudding in large bowl.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in slightly beaten eggs. Gradually add flour mixture; stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: super fast peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and milk.
Pour evenly over butter.
Combine fruit, sugar and water, stir well and spoon evenly over flour mixture.
Do not stir after spooning mixture over flour mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix everything except chocolate bits.
Sprinkle them over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Mix together.
Roll out as desired pie size you want.
Fry in oil.
This is enough dough to make 20 medium size pies.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sour cream.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Blend together.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish; heat at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serve with raw vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: applesauce
directions: Cut and peel the apples.
Put the cut up apples, sugar, cinnamon and water into the saucepan.
Cover and cook on medium heat (simmering) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let the apples cool, then mash with a fork or masher.

title: eggplant creole
directions: Place cooked, drained eggplant in greased baking dish.
In skillet, melt butter and add flour.
Stir until blended.
Add fresh tomatoes, canned tomatoes, onions and green pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add seasoning. Pour over eggplant.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake for an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and taco chip casserole
directions: Crush taco shells or chips in bowl.
Place layer of chips in bottom of greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle layer of chicken over chips.
Pour several spoonfuls soup over the chicken layer. Sprinkle with layer of cheese.
Pour several spoonfuls tomato and green chili (may use El Paso tomato and green chili) over cheese. Repeat steps until dish is full.
Top casserole with additional cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: caramel chex mix
directions: Melt caramels with water.
Mix pecans and cereal together. Pour caramel over cereal mixture.
Pour into buttered baking pan. Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Bake another 10 minutes.
Let cool; break apart.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring butter, brown sugar and syrup to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Mix baking soda and vanilla.
Add soda and vanilla to butter mixture while it is foaming.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in flour, salt and pepper and oil or margarine; baste all over.
While waiting for meat to brown (turn each time), first peel carrots and slice.
Put them in pressure cooker (15 minutes) where meat is cooking.
Then peel potatoes and cut onion. Wait and see if boils over.
Then season with Worcestershire sauce, add water plus tomato sauce.
Then put all vegetables in the cooker.
Cook 15 or 20 minutes depending on your cooker.
First cook until loud noise, turn it down (regular degrees) and count 20 minutes.
Delicious!

title: mexican fudge
directions: Beat eggs; add picante sauce and half of cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle other half of cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares while hot.
Pizza cutter works best.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together flour and sugar. Add the boiling water slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook 15 minutes over hot water. Add to beaten egg yolks. Return to

heat and cook for 2 minutes to thicken the yolks. When thickened, remove from heat and stir in lemon juice and grated rind. Add butter and salt; mix well. Pour into a baked pie shell and cover with meringue made with the egg whites.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Add margarine, Parmesan and eggs to cooked spaghetti.
Form crust in buttered pie pan.
Cook hamburger, onion and peppers; drain.
Add tomatoes, paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt. Heat.
Spread cottage cheese over crust.
Add tomato mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add cheese; bake to melt.

title: prize-winning coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Mix flour and baking powder in bowl.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in coconut extract and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Set oven temperature at 325°.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: pumpkin cheesecake squares
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter in a large bowl.
Add butter; stir until mixture is crunchy.
Press into bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: quick pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Lightly flour and fast fry until golden brown in 1/2 inch shortening.
In baking dish melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup or 1 cup rice over buttered dish.
Slice or chop 2 green peppers, 1 onion and 1 can tomatoes over rice.
Place browned pork chops over mixture.
Slice remaining pepper, onion and tomatoes over pork chops.
Cover. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves six.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in top of double boiler. Add 4 squares of unsweetened chocolate and let melt. Add 3 cups sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, stirring slowly. Add 1/2 teaspoon salt. Slowly stir in 1 can evaporated milk. Cook until slightly thick. Store in jar in refrigerator. Serve on ice cream. Tastes like real Dairy Queen chocolate.

title: tex mex bean soup mix
directions: Combine seasonings in small sealable bag. Combine beans and measure 2 heaping cups into sealable plastic bag.
For gift giving, include packet of beans, seasoning, and recipe. (See Soups, Salads, and Sauces for recipe.)

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in bottom of buttered 8 x 10-inch casserole.
Place cooked chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Place shredded cheese on top and cover with soft bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mother's dumplings
directions: Cover bread with milk.
Cook until this comes to soft boil. Add enough flour to make a dry dough.
Remove from heat; add eggs and nutmeg.
Dough will leave the side of the pan, similar to cream puffs.
Drop by teaspoon into hot soup.
Dumplings will float.

title: joy's pastabazoul
directions: Add all ingredients (excluding cabbage and macaroni) to 2 quarts water.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 hours.
Add cabbage and macaroni.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll biscuits in a cinnamon and sugar mixture.
In a saucepan, cook oleo and brown sugar until melted and combined.
In a Bundt pan, put a layer of cooked mixture, then a layer of cinnamon-sugar covered biscuits, then nuts (optional).
Continue to fill the pan, alternating cooked mixture, nuts and biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lime pie
directions: Make a graham crust in a pie pan.
Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Add green food coloring to desired color. Put in pie crust and top with last cup of Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: crab cakes
directions: Place crab meat in a bowl.
Add wet bread (sprinkle bread with water and press out excess moisture).
Break into very small bits. Add salt, pepper and red pepper to taste.
Add lightly beaten egg, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and mayonnaise.

title: encharitos
directions: Fully cook meat.
Drain by running hot water over meat.
Place meat inside tortillas.
Cover with refried beans.
Fold from left to right, with final fold facing down.
Be sure not to overfill tortillas.
Cover folded tortillas with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cover with desired taco sauce.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stuff bird.
Roast in 375° oven for 3 hours and when the three hours are up - - -get the Hell out of the kitchen because the popcorn is going to blow the butt off the bird!

title: cherry torte
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and cool thoroughly.
Whip 1 pint heavy whipping cream.
Add 2 tablespoons granulated sugar.
Place on top of cake, spreading evenly.
Place cherries on top.
Chill 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: sugar free cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Spoon onto cookie sheet and
bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole supreme
directions: Boil the 2 packages of broccoli.
Drain.
Add the next 5 ingredients; put in a casserole dish and cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Add celery to 4 c. water and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and enough water to cover.
Cook until tender.
Add browned bacon, and soup mix.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cheese that's been cut into cubes.
Add milk and simmer until cheese melts completely.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Using the bacon strips that have been cut in half, secure 9 to 10 green beans into a bundle.
Place bundle in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with oleo, brown sugar, garlic salt and soy sauce.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Stir first 16 ingredients and bring to boil, then add beef and pork.
Return to boil; reduce heat and simmer uncovered 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
When ready, prepare spaghetti, cooked with oil.
Serve chili mixture over the cooked spaghetti. In three separate bowls, prepare the garnishes (remaining ingredients).
These are then served over the chili and spaghetti.

title: wassail
directions: In a large pot, bring to boil all ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Strain and pour into a slow cooker to keep hot.
Serves 20.

title: catfish court bouillon
directions: Cook fish prior to preparing.
Can be prepared 2 ways, broiled with butter, lemon juice and paprika or boiled 20 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast smoothie(makes 1 serving)
directions: Put banana and half the juice (and the cashews, if desired) in a blender or food processor fitted with a steel blade.
Blend, adding remaining juice gradually, until smooth.
Add berries (and yogurt, if desired), and blend thoroughly.
Serve immediately.

title: tamale pie casserole
directions: Fry onions, garlic and meat in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or just a little longer.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a medium skillet, saute onion, garlic, bell pepper and celery in butter about 5 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, bay leaf, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add additional water if needed.
Add thawed shrimp.
Bring mixture to a boil; cook, covered, over medium heat 5 minutes.
Serve Shrimp Creole over white rice. Makes 2 generous servings.

title: light rolls
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; let stand until yeast is dissolved.
Mix all ingredients well together.
Put stiff dough on floured surface and knead well.
Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Put into oiled pans to rise 2 hours, then bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: donuts
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients and add enough flour to make dough stiff,
yet
pliable.
Let
rise
in
a warm place; punch down once or twice.
Roll out and cut.
Let lay 30 to 40 minutes, then fry.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar in frying pan; melt to a light brown syrup.
Add nuts; let cool for a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into a greased pan (not glass).
When cool, remove from pan and break into pieces.

title: peasant potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes & eggs & layer in buttered baking dish alternately with sour cream, salt & pepper, meat, and cheese & crumbs. Pour cream over top and add more cheese & crumbs to top. Bake 30 minutes at 450° or until hot clear through.
* I have never used the cream in this, but I substitute regular milk instead.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let stand 5 minutes before cooking. Cook until it forms a soft ball.
When done, add marshmallows and peanut butter.
Beat until done.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Toss lightly.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Cruzan Seasoning:
Mixture of pond salt and the following herbs:

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water and salt.
Don't overcook. Drain.

title: white chili
directions: Cook chicken in 6 cups water (I usually add 2 chicken bouillon cubes for more flavor).
Cool and debone.
Cook onion in olive oil until tender.
Add garlic, green chilies, cumin, oregano and cayenne pepper and saute.
Mix the mixture with beans, chicken stock, chopped chicken and Monterey Jack cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with sour cream.

title: mozart mozzarella
directions: Brown beef and add onions.
Mix with tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Spread in pan.
Spread cheeses over it.
Lay out crescent rolls and spread with sour cream.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt, pepper, and dry spaghetti seasoning mix. Place in slow cooker. Top with chopped tomatoes.

title: dump cake
directions: Crumb the cake on top of fruit.
Put the butter over cake. Bake at 350° to 375° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown at 450°. Mix margarine and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits.
Serve warm.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients in large bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Spread in jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar in pan.
Bake at 400° for approximately 8 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan, do not overbake.
Cool. Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix gelatin, water and strawberries and let set. Strawberries will thaw in liquid.
Pour on top of cream mixture.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese. Mix well.
Spoon in a greased 2 1/2-quart baking casserole.
Crush crackers and mix with 1/4 cup butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Garnish with lemon twist and parsley, if desired.

title: arkansas rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until rice is tender.
Yields 8 servings.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados.
Add onions, pepper, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Beat until creamy.
Gently fold in tomato.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in stock with onion until soft.
Place in blender and blend quickly, leaving small pieces of broccoli.
Make a roux using butter and flour.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli and stock to roux.
To avoid lumps, stir constantly until thickened.* Thin to preferred consistency with half and half cream.
Add seasonings and wine.

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Combine and chill.
Serve with fresh chopped vegetables. Enjoy.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix and let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Serve over cream cheese.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans and place in large kettle.
Cover with 2 inches of water and soak overnight.
Drain in the morning.
Add 2 quarts of water and a ham hock or ham.
Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 3 hours.
Add onion, tomatoes and seasonings.
Remove ham and cut into pieces.
Return to soup and simmer for 1 hour longer.
Serve with tossed salad and crackers.

title: after dinner coffee
directions: Place brandy and coffee liqueur in cup.
Fill with black coffee.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 1 serving.

title: cinnamon cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over cinnamon graham crackers. Bake at 325 degrees for 10-15 minutes.
Line pan with foil.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, sugar and baking powder together.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Stir to blend.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.
If batter is too thick, spread batter into hot skillet.
If you like thinner pancakes, increase the amount of buttermilk.

title: micro chocolate dipped fruit
directions: Place chocolate chips in micro-safe dish, not too deep.
Add 1 teaspoon vegetable shortening.
Micro on Medium-High power about 4 minutes until melted and smooth.
Stir well and dip fruit.
Place on waxed paper.
Chill.
If chocolate gets too thick, micro.
Also dip nuts and pretzels.

title: father's pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Add melted margarine and mix well. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Add rest of ingredients. Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: In saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar; boil 3 minutes. Add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved. Add cream cheese and stir until mixture is thoroughly combined. Cool until cold, but not congealed.
Fold in apples, nuts, celery and whipped topping. Pour into a 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm. Yields 9 to 12 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
In a mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar.
In a separate bowl, mix together the eggs, vanilla, zucchini, milk and nuts.
Alternate combining the wet and dry ingredients with the creamed mixture.
Spread batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: green beans caesar
directions: Heat beans and 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Cover and cook until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: mjeddrah(pronounced mi-jed-rah)
directions: This is it!
This is the traditional Middle Eastern stew for which Esau sold his birth-right to Jacob.
Taste it and you'll see why!

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in cooking oil in a Dutch oven.
Add water, onion, seasonings and tomato paste.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 to 2 hours. Stir in potatoes, carrots and green pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes. Add more water, if necessary.
Stir in remaining ingredients, cover and simmer for 20 minutes more.
Will serve 10 people.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix together.
Add flour, buttermilk and baking soda.
Mix well as you add in your flavor.
Bake in tube pan.
Grease pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter.
Mix in flour and gradually blend in the chicken broth, half and half and wine.
Cook, stirring for about 3 minutes.
After mixture starts to simmer, stir in 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Measure out 1 cup of sauce and blend in remaining cheese.

title: date pudding
directions: Combine dates and soda; pour boiling water over dates, then set aside. Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Add the date mixture to sugar mixture. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and add milk.
Pour into pastry shell and bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° to 375° and bake 45 minutes, or until done.

title: shrimp and corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon in dutch oven until crisp.
Remove, crumble, and set aside.
Saute onions in 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings until tender.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 15-20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk, corn, and shrimp.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until the shrimp are cooked - about 10 to 15 minutes depending on the size of the shrimp.
Check for seasoning and add if needed.
Use crumbled bacon as a topping for each bowl.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg, extract and almond powder. Gradually add flour, salt, flour and baking powder.
Can knead with hands.
Make balls.
Place on greased pan.
Place whole almond in center.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blueberry cream muffins
directions: Beat
eggs;
add
sugar
slowly.
Add
oil and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream.	Fold in berries.
Bake in muffin tin at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs, sour cream and cream of coconut and beat.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch cake pans. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Remove cake from pans, cool completely and frost with Pina Colada Frosting.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a greased casserole for 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter chips, 1 cup condensed milk and 2 tablespoons butter over low heat. Spread mixture into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Melt chocolate chips, remaining milk and butter. Spread on top of peanut butter mixture.
Chill 2 hours. Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off paper and cut in squares.

title: confetti salad
directions: Drain juice from green beans and set aside.
Drain juice from peas, corn and pimentos.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Add juice from green beans.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry rhubarb cobbler
directions: Spread fruit in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and dot with butter.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Mix 2 1/4 cups flour with salt and sugar in large glass bowl. Sprinkle yeast on the top.
Pour hot water and margarine into the flour mixture and mix well.
Blend to form a ball, then knead on floured surface trying to knead as much of the remaining flour as needed.
Roll dough out onto a greased cookie sheet.
Layer cheese and corned beef down the middle.
Cut slots in the sides of dough and bring across to look like braid, sealing up the insides. Cover and let rise 15 minutes over boiling water.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: brownies with icing
directions: Melt cocoa and margarine.
Mix sugar and eggs, then add cocoa mixture.
Blend in flour mix.
Add vanilla and pecans and spread into a 15 x 12-inch pan.
Cook at 310° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over brownies; rebake until mallow is puffed.
Then frost with icing.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
In a large skillet, place hamburger, rice, tomato sauce, water, carrots, salt and pepper.
Stir to combine.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to simmer. Simmer, covered, over low heat until rice is done and carrots are tender.
Do not stir!
Add water as needed to keep from sticking. Serves 6.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: Boil whole chicken or 4 breasts of chicken until tender.
Take off bone when cool.
Simmer listed ingredients together.
Add chicken to sauce and simmer slowly.
Take a portion of sauce and make a flour and water thickening.
Return to sauce, stirring constantly.
Add cooked mushrooms, if desired.
Serve over noodles or on rolls.
Freezes very well.
A great way to use leftover turkey, too!

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 15-inch dish.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and milk in a bowl.
Pour over melted butter; do not stir.
Use 1 quart fruit and spoon over batter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Spray electric frying pan with Pam.
Saute chicken (cut into pieces) in small quantity of diet Italian dressing.
Add cut up onion and pepper, mushrooms, tomato sauce and zucchini (sliced thin).
Cover and simmer until done.
Yields 2 to 4 servings.

title: crabmeat cream cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except crabmeat and nuts. Finely chop crabmeat in food processor and stir into mixture. Chill. Form 1/2-inch balls and roll in chopped nuts.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips, add salt and pepper.
Brown in a little oil.
When brown add water and tbsp. soy sauce and garlic. Cover and cook 30 minutes on medium-low.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Lay and flatten crescent rolls flat in a 9 X 13 inch pan. Brown sausage and crumble over rolls.
Sprinkle mozzarella cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs with milk, salt, & pepper and pour over. Bake 30-40 minutes at 350 degrees until set.

title: chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook ground beef until browned. Add in onions, green peppers, and celery; cook until tender (about 5 min.). Stir in tomatoes, sauce, water, Worcestershire sauce, and seasonings. Add beans. Bring to a boil, reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Break dried beef into pieces, add onion and pepper.
Warm in double boiler and serve with taco chips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in saucepan and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.

title: orange frost
directions: Mix with electric mixture. Pour into cups and serve immediately.

title: asparagus amandine
directions: Drain cooked asparagus.
Melt butter in small skillet.
Cook almonds over low heat until golden brown, about 5 to 7 minutes; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add salt and lemon juice; pour over hot asparagus.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: nutty raisin stuffing
directions: Place raisins and 3/4 cup water in a small ovenware bowl. Cover with wax paper.
Cook for 2 minutes; set aside.
Place butter, celery and onion in an ovenware dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Continue cooking for 10 minutes, stirring 3 times.
Stir in chicken broth, salt, sage and pepper.
Add bread crumbs, walnuts and raisin-water mixture.
Toss lightly until evenly moist.
Cover with wax paper.
Continue cooking stuffing 7 minutes. Total cooking time: 19 minutes.
Recipe yields 5 cups or enough to stuff a 6 pound turkey.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream
butter
gradually;
add sugar beating well after each addition.
Combine	flour
and soda; add to creamed mixture. Alternately
put
in sour cream, mixing well after each addition. Stir
in flavoring.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch
tube
pan.
Bake
at
350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes
or until
a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Then remove.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart round casserole dish. In large bowl with a fork, mix flour and next 4 ingredients with pastry blender.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in raisins.
Beat eggs in a small bowl with a fork and remove 1 tablespoon and save.
Stir into flour mixture just until flour is moistened (dough will be sticky).
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead and shape into ball.
Place in a casserole.
Cut a cross in center of dough.
Brush dough with saved egg.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: lo-cal chicken salad
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 3-quart saucepan with just enough water to cover. Add the salt. Bring to a boil.

Lower heat, cover and simmer until chicken is no longer pink when pierced with a fork. Remove chicken to platter to cool. In a large mixing bowl, combine the pineapple, celery, onions, oil, soy sauce and vinegar. When the chicken is cool enough to handle, cut it into 3/4-inch cubes. Add the cubed chicken to the pineapple mixture and toss to mix thoroughly.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake 400 degrees - 20-25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter. Add cooked rice and pour into buttered casserole dish. Add broccoli and soup.
Mix well. Sprinkle cheese on top or mix in Cheez Whiz. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This recipe can be doubled.

title: cheese soup
directions: Bring to boil first four ingredients and cook for twenty minutes, covered. Add carrots, potatoes and mixed vegetables. Cover and cook for 30 minutes. Add cream of chicken soup and Velveeta cheese, heat until cheese is melted. Serve hot.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop rounded spoonfuls on lightly greased pans.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: green beans
directions: Wash and snap green beans.
Put in pot.
Put water over top of beans and cook on medium heat (or medium-high) until all of water just cooked out.
Just before all water is gone, I sprinkle about 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar in beans.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place cooked chicken in bottom of casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream and spread over chicken.
Top with crackers and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Pour melted oleo over top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan fudge pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook for 25 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer everything and let set overnight.
Don't mix until ready to serve.

title: knock you nakeds
directions: Combine and mix well the dry cake mix, nuts, 1/3 cup milk and margarine.
Press half of the mixture into bottom of greased 8 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place cooked, cut up chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream and broth; pour over chicken.
Spread 2 packages crushed crackers over top. Pour melted margarine over crackers and sprinkle poppy seed over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat with mixer.
Chill before serving.
Great with pretzels!

title: dark (christmas) fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well; put into greased pan.
Cook at 325° until well done.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Spread marshmallows in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix cake mix (use Betty Crocker yellow cake mix) according to directions.
Pour over marshmallows in pan.
Mix together rhubarb, sugar and Jell-O.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot mexican cornbread and meat
directions: Saute meat, onion, pimento and bell pepper.
Add soup, chili powder and peppers.
Mix all cornbread ingredients together. Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of cornbread mixture, hamburger meat, and rest of cornbread mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender in boiling water; drain.
Combine with onions, peppers and celery; set aside.
Combine and boil for 1 minute your soup, vinegar, oil, sugar, mustard and sauce.
Cool. Pour over the vegetables; toss lightly.
A real good Christmas salad.

title: easy beef jerky
directions: Cut strips of meat 1 to 1 1/2 inches wide.
Trim off all fat. Lay meat in a bowl in layers, adding seasoning as you go.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Take meat and blanch in hot water for 15 to 20 seconds.
Place meat strips on a cookie sheet and place in oven.
Set temperature on lowest setting.
Leave door ajar. Cook 8 to 16 hours or until meat turns black.
After jerky cools it can be stored in a sealed jar.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients; stir in creamed mixture.
Form into tiny balls.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Put water, oil, lemon juice, salt, onion, pepper and fajita seasoning in frying pan.
Cook on medium high heat until onions and peppers are slightly tender.
Add chicken and cook until all pink coloring is gone.
Remove from heat and spoon fajitas into tortillas.
Add the toppings of your choice.
Enjoy!

title: sausage strata
directions: Spread butter on bread.
Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Crumble sausage into skillet.
Cook gently, turning to keep it in small pieces until no longer pink.
Lift out of skillet with slotted spoon; spread over bread.
Discard fat.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.

title: banana orange frost
directions: Mix orange juice, milk, banana and half the sherbet in a blender on high speed until smooth.
Pour into tall glasses; top each with a scoop of remaining sherbet.
Makes 3 servings (1 cup each).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
Drain well.
In bowl, beat eggs and add remaining ingredients, except bread and cheese.
In buttered 2-quart shallow casserole dish, layer bread, squash and cheese. Repeat each layer.
Top with remaining bread.
Dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all
ingredients
in
large mixing container.
Make sure all lumps dissolve.
Store
in large jar with lid.
Use 1 heaping tablespoon per cup of hot water.
Makes 200 cups.

title: crunchy nut cookies
directions: Cream sugars and Crisco. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed sugars and Crisco. Add nuts. Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes or until done.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in flavorings and coconut.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Cook cake mix by directions on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool, leaving in pan.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Mix next 2 ingredients and pour over cake.
Mix last 2 items and spread over top.
Chill.

title: grandma shunk's sugar cookies
directions: Cream
both
sugars, shortening, eggs, oil and vanilla. Mix flour,
cream of tartar, soda and salt in a separate bowl. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.	Dough is soft and must be chilled overnight.

title: avocado chip dip
directions: Halve and peel avocado, reserving 1 shell.
Cube avocado and put into container of an electric blender.
Add lemon juice, onion, mayonnaise, Tabasco and salt; process until pureed.
To serve, pile avocado mixture into reserved shell.
Place on a serving dish and surround with potato chips for dipping.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: refreshing jello mold dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in large bowl. Stir in cold water.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in ice cream until melted.
Pour into any mold.

title: swedish overnight cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and syrup.
Cream until light.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add to butter mixture and mix well.
Add nuts and mix well.
Make into 2 rolls and place in fridge overnight.
Slice and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: italian salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
During last 6 minutes, cook broccoli in same water.
Rinse in cold water, drain.
Combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup cheese.
Toss; add salad dressing, toss; add remaining cheese.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Beat
egg
yolks
with	sugar
until
smooth and thick. Drain pineapple
and
stir
syrup and lemon juice in yolk mixture.
Cook over
hot water, stirring constantly, until thick enough to coat spoon.
Remove from heat; stir in pineapple and cool.
Beat
egg whites
until definite peaks stand up.
Beat cream until
it holds shape.
Gently fold egg whites and cream into
pineapple mixture. Put crushed vanilla wafers in bottom of quart size refrigerator tray and spoon pineapple mixture on top.
Freeze until firm. Serves 6.

title: paul's pumpkin bars
directions: Beat in mixing bowl until light and fluffy, eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and soda.

title: turketti
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add turkey, pimento, pepper and onion to noodles.
Place in a greased casserole.
Pour soup and broth mixture over casserole; season.
Add part of cheese to mixture; sprinkle cheese over top.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: bob wade (deer) tamales
directions: Place roasts in separate kettles; cover with water and boil until tender.
Reserve pork broth.
After meat is cool, grind fine.
Melt 1 pound lard in large kettle and combine ground meat; mix well.
Add cumin, peppers, garlic, 1/2 jar of chili powder, 2 to 4 tablespoons salt, picante sauce and green chilies if desired. Stir until well mixed.
If mixture seems dry, add pork broth until moist.
Simmer uncovered until flavors are absorbed.
Skim off any excess grease and save for masa.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add well
beaten
eggs.
Chop nuts and fruit.
Mix with part flour and baking powder and add to butter and egg mixture.
Grease pan and
line
with
brown paper. Grease paper only on bottom of pan.
Put
in cold oven and bake for 30 minutes at 300°, then turn to
for 2 1/2 hours. Makes a 5 pound cake.
For a more moist
cake,
add
1 cup jelly.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Layer ingredients in a shallow dish or 9 x 9-inch square Pyrex.
Serve cold with corn chips or Doritos.

title: homemade soup
directions: Remove skins from tomatoes by placing them in boiling water for one minute, then put in cold water.
Remove tomato cores and then measure out 2 gallons of tomatoes which should be put in the blender for a brief time.
(You might also prefer blending peppers and onions.)
Add all other ingredients and cook in an open pot for thirty minutes.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Cook eggplant in small amount of salted water.
Drain well. In saucepan, melt 1/2 cup margarine and saute onions and green peppers.
Add sugar, salt and flour, stirring to blend.
Add tomatoes.
Cook, stirring, 5 minutes.
Add eggplant and cornbread. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In a 1-quart shallow casserole dish, combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon.
In medium bowl, mix remaining 2/3 cup baking mix with brown sugar.
Cut in I Can't Believe It's Not Butter until mixture is the size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto peaches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into crust comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Dice bananas and place on top of crust.
Place 1/2-inch slices of ice cream (slightly softened) on top of bananas.
Sprinkle with nuts and freeze.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pie filling, pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt, pepper, celery and 1 1/2 cups water.
Simmer for 20 minutes covered.
Add bean sprouts and heat.
Combine 2 tablespoons water, cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar and brown gravy sauce.
Add to hamburger mixture.
Cook until thick.
Serve over cooked rice and chow mein noodles

title: almond joy candy
directions: Heat the batter and milk until batter is melted.
Add coconut. Cool completely in fridge.
Ball this mixture up.
Next, melt the chips and paraffin.
Dip candy in the melted chocolate.
Cool before serving.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix.
Spoon over chicken and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peach sherbet
directions: Heat sugar and water to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and syrup; cool to room temperature.
Transfer to blender. Add peaches; blend until smooth.
Refrigerate until cold.
Stir in milk, then freeze.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.
Serve with sesame crackers.

title: shrimp mold(dip)
directions: Chop onion and celery well.
Heat soup and water; bring to boil.
Take off stove.
Add cream cheese.
Mix gelatin with 1/2 cup of cold water.
Put in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Fold in remaining ingredients and pour in mold.
Chill overnight.

title: plain cake
directions: Beat egg whites in last.
Pour in batter last.
Bake at 350°.

title: homemade rice pudding
directions: Preheat the oven.
Put the 4 cups of water in a medium size pan and bring to a boil.
Add the salt and shortening.
Add the entire box of rice.
Stir.
Cook rice for 20 to 30 minutes until tender. Pour hot rice into a large, deep dish casserole dish, with glass lid (3-quart size or slightly larger).
Add 1 stick butter or margarine.
Stir until melted.
Add milk and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and stir.
Add vanilla flavoring, making sure it disappears, then add the raisins.
Cover with the glass lid which is excellent for checking on your pudding so that it does not boil over.

title: goof balls
directions: Melt the caramels, butter and milk in a double boiler.
Dip marshmallows in the mixture, then roll in the cereal.
Let cool.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat oil and eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to egg mixture alternately with milk.
Cook at 275°
for more than an hour until done in 2 greased 8-inch pans.

title: orange salad(weight watchers recipe; 50 calories per serving.)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate overnight.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients; press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with sugar and prick with fork.
Bake in 300° oven for 50 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Add all ingredients in bowl.
Toss and serve.
May also be served hot.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients until fluffy.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Mix until blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.
Makes about 100 cookies.
Good plain or with a powdered sugar glaze.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugars.
Beat eggs and salt together and add to creamed mixture.
Add oil and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to first mixture.
If you wish to roll the dough and cut out the cookies, refrigerate dough for an hour.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Spread oil in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Empty cake mix in pan. Add pudding, eggs, water and chocolate bits.
Mix with a fork until blended.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.
Cut in squares.

title: simple peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Pour drained peaches into a 7x11x2
inch baking pan (or pan of approximate size).
Place the bread pieces on top of the peaches, covering top. Combine the sugar, cinnamon, and egg in a 4-cup microwavable bowl. Stir to mix and then add the butter.
Place in microwave and cook on high for about 1 minute or until the butter is melted.
Pour this mixture over the top of the bread.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine in boiling water.
Combine soup, cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in celery, onions and shrimp, then gelatine mixture.
Pour into glass or plastic mold and chill until set.
(Metal molds may discolor shellfish/mayo mixtures.)
To serve, unmold and offer with crackers or heavy chips.

title: potato ripple soup
directions: Bring first four ingredients to rolling boil.
Beat eggs and thicken with flour and soda.
Slowly pour into boiling potatoes and mix a few minutes.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Bring water to a boil with onion, salt, sugar and pepper. Remove from heat.
Combine cornmeals and add 1/3 to water in thin stream, stirring constantly, until very thick.
Vigorously stir in rest of cornmeal.
Cool to room temperature.
Form cornmeal mixture into 3-inch rounds 1/2-inch thick.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, Italian dressing and grated Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Steam broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain and allow to cool.
Add broccoli, drained rotini pasta, finely chopped crab meat, green peppers and onion to cheese mixture.
Toss slightly. Chill overnight or at least 4 hours.
Garnish with green onion slices.

title: wiener bean pot
directions: Combine ingredients in a 2-quart casserole or bean pot.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 1 hour.
Serve.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients;	add
all the liquid at once and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured pans and bake about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken california blend casserole
directions: Put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put vegetables on top of chicken.
Add onion.
Layer cheese on top.
Put dressing on top. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle with either crumbled potato chips of bread crumbs.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and shape into ball.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Marinate cooked macaroni mixed with lemon juice and vegetable oil overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaf with crackers.
Serves 12.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Cook in oven at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter or margarine in microwave, stirring often.
Add cocoa, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: Bake eggplant at 400° until charred on the outside and soft on the inside.
Cool and remove skin.
Chop coarsely, place in colander to drain.
Mash or puree eggplant in blender.
Stir in mayonnaise and 2 eggs, finely chopped or minced.
Add olive oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Place in an oiled mold and chill. Unmold on a platter and decorate with thin strips of green pepper, lemon wedges and sliced onion rings.
Serve on crackers.

title: graham cracker cherry pudding
directions: Melt
margarine
in
a	12-inch Dutch oven and mix with crumbs.
Mix drained cherries
and	nuts.
Save
cherry juice. Layer in Dutch oven, alternating
crumb
mix
with cherry mix. Make sure you end with crumb
mix
on
top.
Pour cherry juice over the top.
Cook 35 minutes with
12 coals on top and 10 on bottom.

title: ginny's tortilla cheese rings
directions: Have cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and picante at room temperature.
Mix very well.
Add onion, garlic salt and jalapeno; mix well.
Spread on tortilla and roll lightly.
Put back in refrigerator.
Chill and then cut with electric knife.
Can freeze.

title: burrito bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Mix Bisquick, water and beans; spread into pie plate.
Layer remaining ingredients on bean mixture and bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: pork milano
directions: In hot oil, in large frying pan, brown pork well.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Saute until tender.
Mix in mushrooms and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, for 25 minutes.
Blend in soup and milk.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In large saucepan melt shortening and add brown sugar.
Blend well and remove from heat.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Mix well.
Spread in well-greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: burgundy mushrooms
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, combine all ingredients. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 3 hours.

title: lemonade syrup
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool completely.
Stir in lemon juice.
Store in covered jar in fridge.
Use in lemonade or lemonade spritzer.

title: crazy baked beans
directions: Drain all but last can of beans and mix well.
Dice bacon and brown.
Saute onion in bacon grease.
Drain and mix 1/2 with beans.
Make sauce with the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Add to beans and sprinkle remaining bacon on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mucho-gusto-taco
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add remaining ingredients except chips. Heat on low or in crock-pot until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: sweet-n-sour sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, stirring until thickened. Flavor to suit your taste with horseradish, spicy mustard, soy sauce, more ketchup, etc.
Make several flavors or increase recipe depending on number of people to be served.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix with spoon 50 times.
300 people can eat these.
Bake 10 hours in hot oven.
They taste kind of chocolatey and pretty good.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: In a saucepan over low heat combine Cheddar cheese and butter. Stir occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion and salt.
Fold in potatoes and turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot butter; sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
You can use as stuffing for twice baked potatoes.

title: peas and bread
directions: Add soda to buttermilk and set aside.
Mix cornmeal, flour, salt, eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add peas, green chilies, corn, meat and all the grated cheese except a small amount for top. Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pudding cake
directions: In separate bowl, mix dry cake mix and butter until crumbly; set aside.
In large bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Place into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put crumbly mixture on top and swirl in. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hash-brown casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Put mixture in a large, greased casserole.
Bake about 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Add remaining; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill several hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sally's clam chowdah
directions: In pan, place clams, celery, onions, clam juice and 1 pint of chicken broth and cook for about 5 minutes. Make a cream sauce from the butter, flour and remaining chicken broth. Add this to the clam mixture; also add the potatoes. Cook until potatoes are tender; season with bay leaf and thyme. Add cup of cream. Heat just before serving. Add salt and pepper to your taste.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix all together in food processor. Whip until thick. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt butter in a large baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together (makes stiff batter).
Pour over margarine. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: turkey noodle parmesan
directions: Prepare noodles.
Combine soup, milk, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Add noodles and turkey.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Cook
acini
de
pepe
according
to directions on box. Drain. Saute
onion,
pepper
and celery.
Mix acini de pepe, sauteed vegetables and Hellmann's mayonnaise as you would in a salad.
Add 1
pound
of
small scallops and mix.
Put in a 2 quart casserole.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for
about 30 minutes until crumbs are brown and casserole is bubbly.

title: mildred essick's chocolate icing
directions: Cream the margarine and egg together.
Add sugar and cocoa and beat.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Frost when cake is cool.

title: halloween brownie pumpkin
directions: Bake brownie mix as directed on a 12-inch greased pizza pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with orange frosting.
Use dark brown M&M's for eyes, nose and eye brows.
Use candy corn for mouth. Kids love it.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: 5 hour oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix gently but well. Put in 3-quart casserole and cover.
Bake in 275° oven for 5 hours.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: reese's fudge
directions: Melt butter. Stir in peanut butter.
Mix together cocoa mix and sugar.
Put into a buttered pan. Cool and cut.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix gelatins together and add boiling water; stir until completely dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce and stir this until thoroughly mixed.
Add pineapple with juice, pecans and celery. Pour in mold or 12 individual molds and chill until firm.

title: apple orchard punch
directions: In large bowl combine apple juice, cranberry cocktail and orange juice; stir to dissolve.
Slowly add ginger ale.
Slice the apple thinly, forming whole apple slices.
Separate the orange slices and add to bowl.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Cook the rice according to directions on the package.
Add the chicken, mushrooms, pimentos, green pepper, parsley, soups and broth to rice and mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole dish and cover top with sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda. Cream Crisco and sugars. Add egg, water and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and oatmeal; stir until well blended. Stir in raisins and pecans. Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pack into graham cracker box. Store in refrigerator one day and night before cutting.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend eggs, salad oil and carrots.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Put in 3 cake tins (8-inch).
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: cranberry swirl cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating in well.
Add dry ingredients, sour cream and flavoring, mixing quickly and thoroughly.

title: apple jelly and cream cheese(appetizer)
directions: Mix well and when ready to use, pour over Philly cream cheese and serve with Ritz crackers as spread.

title: mildred's chicken pie
directions: Place chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle eggs over chicken.
Mix chicken broth with celery soup; pour over chicken and eggs.
Mix margarine into flour; add milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix together; beat well.
Place in greased and floured pan. Bake in slow oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cooked beets
directions: Stir together the sugar, vinegar, water and salt; bring to a boil.
Add to red beets.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat oil and eggs until foamy.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° until done.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bowl; add Crisco.
Mix with fork until crumbly.
Add ice water one tablespoon at a time.
Make 2 equal balls of dough.
Roll crust between wax paper.

title: chocolate macaroon cake
directions: Coconut Mixture:
Beat egg white with 1 teaspoon vanilla until soft mounds form.
Add 1/2 cup sugar gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.
Stir in coconut, 1 tablespoon flour and half teaspoon salt.
Set aside.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute oil, onion, garlic and green pepper. Add to beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 1 hour.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Any type of meat can be marinated in this sauce up to 78 hours in the refrigerator.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together vegetables, soup and chicken.
Divide mixture between 2 of the 4 pie shells.
Place remaining 2 pie shells, one each, on top of the filled pies.
Put a few holes in each top. Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and pull into small pieces.
Reserve broth from cooked chicken breasts.
Place chicken breasts in bottom of Pyrex dish (9 x 12-inch).
Mix together cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour this over chicken breasts.
Mix 1 1/4 chicken broth and 3/4 stick melted butter.
Pour over one package of herbs and stuffing and place on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Make a batter of the first 6 ingredients (mix well).
Pour 1/2 of batter into square pan.
Crumble hamburger over this.
Sprinkle green chilies over meat.
Then add cheese over all.
Pour other half of batter over this.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spicy green beans *
directions: Heat wok over high heat.
Add oil and heat.
Add ginger and garlic and stir-fry 30 seconds.
Add beans.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add sugar, sherry, salt, chili paste with garlic and soy sauce.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes longer.
In separate dish, combine cornstarch and water to make smooth paste.
Add to wok and cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Remove from heat. Add sesame oil.
Let cool.
Chill 2 or more hours.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: scrambled dog
directions: Cut hot dog into slices or small pieces.
Break eggs into small bowl.
Add milk; stir with fork.
Stir in hot dog and cheese.
In a small skillet, heat butter or margarine until bubbly.
Pour in egg mixture.
When eggs look cooked around the edges, gently push a pancake turner across the bottom of skillet. Keep cooking and pushing until the eggs are set, but still moist.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add 1/2 cup tomato sauce and taco mix. Blend well.
Line bottom of 8-inch square baking dish with 2 cups corn chips, coarsely crushed.
Then crush remaining chips; set aside.
Combine remaining tomato sauce and beans.
