Spread meat mixture over chips, then spoon bean mixture over meat.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese and 1/2 cup remaining corn chips on top and bake 5 minutes more.
Serve with salad.

title: fudge meltaways
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and 1 square chocolate in a saucepan. Blend granulated sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla, egg, crumbs, coconut and nuts into chocolate mixture.
Mix and press into ungreased pan, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch or square 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch. Refrigerate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost spinach and drain well.
Combine with all ingredients. Mix well and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables or crackers.

title: polka-dot baked macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook macaroni as label directs; drain. Meanwhile, in a saucepan, melt 1/4 cup of butter.
Stir in flour and then soup and milk.
Cook, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Combine macaroni, soup mixture, 3/4 cup cheese and 1/2 package of peas and carrots.
Turn into 2-quart greased casserole. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Place other 1/2 package of peas and carrots in a small casserole with 1 tablespoon of butter, salt and water.
Bake small casserole, covered, and macaroni casserole, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
When done, spoon the 1/2 package of peas and carrots around casserole to make a colorful wreath. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream cheese pineapple biscuits
directions: Press fingers into the center of each biscuit, making a deep indentation about 1 3/4-inches wide.
Fill indentations with cream cheese.
Arrange well drained crushed pineapple around outside edge of cream cheese.
Sprinkle with ground cinnamon.
Bake as directed on biscuit package.

title: country breakfast
directions: In nonstick 12-inch skillet over medium heat, use 1 teaspoon hot salad oil to cook Canadian bacon slices or ham until lightly brown.
Remove to plate.
In same skillet in 1 teaspoon hot salad oil, cook hash brown potatoes until golden brown on bottom, without stirring, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Make potatoes like a big pancake.
Put on 12-inch platter.
Add 1 teaspoon salad oil to skillet slide potato pancake into skillet.
Arrange Canadian bacon slices and tomato slices in circle on top of potatoes, overlapping slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time; break eggs into a saucer.
Now slip the eggs into skillet on top of potatoes on side of skillet. Sprinkle eggs and tomato with salt and pepper.
Cover skillet and cook until the eggs are firm.
Garnish with chopped parsley. Serves 6.

title: microwave mornay sauce
directions: Cook milk in 1-quart glass bowl on High until hot, about 2 minutes. Set aside and keep warm.

title: super luscious freeze
directions: Combine milk and pineapple with juice. In a 5-quart container, combine pineapple mixture and enough orange soda to fill container. Freeze until firm.

title: sauerkraut dip
directions: Drain sauerkraut, but do not squeeze.
Chop corned beef fine. Cook sauerkraut, cream cheese and corned beef over medium-low heat; stir often.
Add small amounts of sour cream at a time.
You may add more if it is too thick.
Once it is all melted and cooked together, serve with bread cubes, crackers or favorite snack. This dip can be saved and reheated in microwave also.
Keep warm in small crock-pot as you serve.

title: blond brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add eggs, vanilla and sugar; mix well. Combine dry ingredients; add to the first mixture.
(Addition of 3/4 cup chopped nuts is optional.)
Spread into greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed pork tenderloin
directions: Stuff with dressing or Stove Top stuffing.
Roll up and tie each end and down the middle.
Brown lightly in frying pan.
Place in
a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with chicken broth. Cover with foil. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove the stuffed tenderloin. Thicken the juices in the pan.
Cut the tenderloin in 1 1/2-inch slices. Serve with rice or mashed potatoes, vegetables or salad. Serves 6 to 8.

title: yellow casserole
directions: Combine squash, water and salt in a pan; bring to a boil, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain.
Saute onion and yellow pepper in butter 3 minutes.
Combine melted magarine, egg, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add all other ingredients. Place in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: rolls
directions: Mix well and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: butter nut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Mix soda and salt in buttermilk. Add flour and other ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: faux pas swiss steak
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except spaghetti sauce; mix until well blended. Form into 6 patties, 1/2-inch thick. In a large skillet over medium heat, place 2 tablespoons olive or peanut oil and cook meat patties until brown on both sides. Add spaghetti sauce and simmer on low heat 15 to 20 minutes. Let sit in skillet 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese. Stir in flour and salt; mix well.
Shape into miniature muffin cups.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix together in casserole dish with tight lid.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.
No peeking.
If you omit onion soup and water, you can just use two cans of soup.
Spread on top of meat and cover with foil and don't peek.
Serve with noodles or potatoes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: french onion soup
directions: You will need cup/bowl.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Mix all the ingredients except apples.
Roll out dough and cut around a saucer for a circle.
Put fruit.
I use dried apples that have been seasoned with sugar and spices.
Fold over and crimp edges with fork.
Fry in deep fat.
Sprinkle with sugar after frying.

title: crusty potatoes
directions: Mix together potatoes, salt, pepper, sour cream, soup and diced onions.
Put the corn flakes and melted oleo on top.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 12-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
This is a good appetizer for dipping carrot sticks, cauliflower, cucumbers and radishes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together the oatmeal and boiling water; let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening and both sugars.
Add eggs.
Mix in all dry ingredients.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan (spray Pam can be used).
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Place chicken in large, rectangular dish.
Cover with mushrooms, both cans of soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: biscuit barbecups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Cook 1 minute to blend flavors, stirring constantly.

title: caesar salad
directions: Cut up lettuce.
Sprinkle cheese over lettuce.
Combine rest of ingredients except croutons; pour over lettuce.
Add croutons.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg, then bran; mix thoroughly. Combine water and bananas; add alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly; add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in paper-lined loaf pan in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Any type of bran may be used.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with cooked, cut up chicken.
Mix together soup, sour cream, and milk or chicken broth.
Spread mixture over chicken.
Combine melted margarine, crushed crackers, and poppy seed.
Sprinkle over creamed chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered, until bubbly.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Pour into well-greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Cool; add whipped topping.
Ready to eat.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Grate sweet potatoes into milk, then add everything in order. Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: washington cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and melted margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Increase oven temperature to 450°.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and flour, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Pour mixture over crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 250°; continue baking 25 to 30 minutes. Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool before removing.
Chill. Before serving, top with pie filling.

title: cornbread biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 475°.
Stir together the cornmeal, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cut in the shortening until the mixture is like meal.
Add the buttermilk and knead very lightly, only until mixed.
Pour out onto a floured board and roll out to about 1/3-inch thickness.
Use a biscuit cutter to cut biscuits. Gently reroll the scraps and cut more biscuits from them.
Place the biscuits on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake for 12 minutes until brown and slightly crunchy on the outside.
Yield: 12 to 15 biscuits.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a microwaveproof dish. Cook on High power for approximately 15 minutes or until done.

title: baked steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and sear in hot fat.
Place in crock-pot. In mixing bowl, combine mushroom soup, onion soup and 1 1/2 cans of water.
Mix well and pour over meat.
Cook on low all day. (May also be cooked on stove in heavy skillet or in oven.)

title: *banana split dessert
directions: Mix 1 stick butter or margarine with graham cracker crumbs. Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Beat the powdered sugar, 2 sticks butter or margarine and eggs for 15 minutes with electric mixer. Spread over crumb mixture.
Drain pineapple; save juice.
Slice bananas into saved juice and drain.
Place banana slices on top of beaten mixture.
Spoon on pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over all. Sprinkle top with nuts and cherries.
Chill.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased pan, 5 x 13. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup cheese.
Bake in 3-quart casserole, uncovered, for 15 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake, uncovered, for at least 1 hour.

title: simple salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar with a tight-fitting lid; shake until blended.
Store in the refrigerator.
Shake well before serving.
Drizzle over salad.

title: one-foot-in-the-fire fudge cake
directions: Combine water and chocolate in a small heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat; cool.
Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Mix just until blended.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 19 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
Spread Fluffy White Filling between layers.
Spread Chocolate Frosting on top and sides of cake.
Yield:
one 3-layer cake.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Remove	tough
ends of flower stalks and wash broccoli. Cut into flowerets.
Place flowerets in a large, shallow dish and set aside.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While still hot, spread marshmallows over cake.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Let cool.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased and floured bread pan.
Let rise in pan for 10 minutes, then bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
All the alcohol is evaporated; quick and easy with soup.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar, salt, butter and flour.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 325° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix vinegar, salad oil and sugar.
Pour over kraut mixture. Let chill.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Beat sugar into egg.
Add vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Fold in apples.
Spread in buttered pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients; mix together with a fork.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: santa fe grilled chicken sandwiches
directions: Heat grill.
Mix seasonings; sprinkle on each chicken breast. Place chicken on grill over medium coals.
Grill 6 minutes on each side or until cooked through.
Top with cheese slice.
Grill until cheese is melted.
Cut bread into 4 sandwich size sections.
For each sandwich, top bottom half of bread with lettuce, chicken, 1 tablespoon salsa or picante and top half of bread.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: emily's bean soup
directions: Wash all beans thoroughly; drain and place in a 4-quart kettle with 5 cups water.
Bring to a rapid boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.

title: green beans and almonds
directions: Cook beans in salt water 5 to 7 minutes; drain.
Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine or butter in skillet; add nuts.
Use low heat.
Stir occasionally 5 to 7 minutes until browned.
Stir in remaining salt and pepper.
Pour over beans.
Toss to mix.
Yields 12 servings.

title: meal-in-a-muffin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Shred carrot and apple in food processor.
Set aside.
Process the oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add the carrot, apple and remaining ingredients.
Divide the batter among greased muffin tins, filling them 3/4 full and bake in preheated oven until a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Arrange ingredients, in order mentioned, in layers.
Top with onion powder and shredded cabbage or onion rings.
Make in either large salad bowl or cake pan.
Can double.
Make an additional 7 layers for large group.
Chill overnight.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add oleo on low speed.

title: oriental cabbage slaw
directions: Mix and chill dressing overnight: vinegar, oil, pepper, salt, sugar, onion and chicken seasoning packet from Ramen noodles.

title: great depression cake
directions: In large saucepan simmer the first 5 ingredients for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool 10 minutes.
Blend together remaining ingredients and stir into mixture.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool and dust with powdered sugar if desired.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine the flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together the shortening and peanut butter.
Add both kinds of sugar.
Cream well.
Add the egg, vanilla and milk.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Roll balls in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and place a Hershey candy Kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so that cookie cracks around the edge. Return to oven and bake for 3 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Line casserole sides and bottom with chips. Add other ingredients.
Pour over chips.
Put grated cheese over top.
Cook 30 minutes or until bubbly on sides of casserole.

title: chinese chicken with hoisin sauce
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite-size pieces and combine with soy sauce, sherry and cornstarch in bowl.
Cut up vegetables to taste; use whatever you like, 1 bunch scallions, 1 red pepper and 1 bunch broccoli is enough for 3 hearty eaters.
Stir-fry veggies in 1 tablespoon oil for about 2 minutes.
Start scallions first; do not overcook! Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to veggies and dish out into bowl. Stir-fry chicken in 3 tablespoons oil until it turns color.
Add cooked veggies and nuts if you want and then add hoisin sauce and mix well.
Serves 3 or 4.
Easy to double.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix together soups, broth and Ro-Tel (cook chicken and retain broth for use in this recipe); heat thoroughly.
Layer in order: crushed Doritos, soup mixture, chicken, onion and cheese.
Make 2 layers.
Top layer should be Doritos and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400° until cheese melts.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread bean dip in bottom of dish.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning mix; mix well.
Spread over bean dip.
Grate cheese on top; add remaining toppings.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: grandma jacobs' cabbage patch soup
directions: Brown meat, celery and onion.
Add the rest of the ingredients; simmer for 2 hours.

title: mama's nut rolls
directions: Sift
flour,
sugar and salt, cut in shortening to size of peas.
Dissolve
yeast in warm milk and add beaten eggs to mixture.
Add
to
flour mixture and knead until it comes away clean
from
hands.
Place in large bowl, cover with tea towel and place
in cold spot overnight (refrigerator will do).
In the olden
days
Mama
put
the bowl on the back porch.
When ready to use, let dough stand at room temperature until soft. Cut
into 4
sections
on a floured surface and roll out each one.
Spread nut filling over all of the dough surface.
Roll as for jelly roll, brush top with beaten egg.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger. Pour off excess fat. Add taco seasoning and water; mix well. Take rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar, water, vinegar and salt together; pour over vegetables.
Mix all together and let stand in refrigerator. Keeps well and crisp for a couple of weeks.

title: four bean salad
directions: Cook vinegar, sugar, oil and salt until it boils.
Cool. Drain beans.
(Rinse kidney beans.)
Pour oil mixture over beans and chopped vegetables.
Let set overnight.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, flour, onions, salt and pepper.
Stir in vegetables.
In large skillet, heat 1/4 cup oil.
Drop batter by tablespoons into hot oil.
Cook about 1 minute on each side or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot with Red Pepper Mayonnaise.

title: dotty's sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Set aside rest of the can of tomato sauce for later.

title: fresh tomato relish
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes fine; drain in a colander 2 to 3 hours. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Store in a cool place.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

In large bowl, add all ingredients. Toss in bowl until vegetables are evenly coated. Arrange vegetables in 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake uncovered, stirring once for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in crock-pot on high until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix together cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
In separate bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Combine these ingredients with Cool Whip and cream together.
Pour into flower pot and refrigerate overnight.
Next day (to prevent soggy dirt), crunch cookies in plastic bag with rolling pin and sprinkle over top of pudding.
Add flower bunch and place in center of table.

title: shrimp (crab or lobster) dip
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers.

title: chocolate milkshake
directions: Combine syrup, milk and ice cream in a blender.
Mix until smooth and frothy.
Pour into large glasses; garnish with whipped cream, grated chocolate or a marshmallow.
Serves 4.

title: veggie delight
directions: Preheat frying pan to medium heat.
Cook onion in Pam until tender.
Add other ingredients and cook until tender, about 15 to 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, salt and soda.
Add egg and buttermilk until it is right consistency to hold its shape when rolled into a ball.
Mix in onion.
Shape into balls about 1 to 2 inches across. Drop into hot fat in which fish has been cooked.
Deep-fry until brown and crispy.
Drain on paper.
Serve hot.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs and oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1/2 cup nuts and bananas.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost; sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving half the juice.
Combine pineapple and reserved juice with next 4 ingredients in serving dish, mixing well.
Chill until partially set.
Add bananas, mixing well. Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken and wine sauce casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine all ingredients except preserves and mix well.
Mold into ring and chill. Fill with preserves.
Serve with crackers.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender.
Drain and keep hot.
In a mixing bowl, combine 1 cup of cheese with the flour, onion, mustard, salt and pepper. Add to the hot macaroni and mix well.
Transfer to a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour the milk over the macaroni.
Top with remaining cheese and dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes or until the macaroni is firm and the top is golden brown.

title: stir-fried chicken
directions: Heat oil at a medium heat in a skillet.
Add garlic and chicken.
Cook until chicken is white.
Add vegetables and cook until desired tenderness of vegetables.
Serve stir-fry over 1 cup of steaming rice.
Heat teriyaki sauce in microwave.
Drizzle over the stir-fry.

title: dilled cucumber salad
directions: Spread yogurt thickly over several layers of paper towels; cover with another layer of paper towels.
Let stand 5 minutes. Scrape yogurt into a medium bowl.
Add cucumbers, green onions and pepper, stirring well.
Fold in dill.
Cover and chill 1 hour. Yield:
4 servings.

title: apricot bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Add oil and soda mixed with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Stir in eggs and baby food.
Fold in nuts.
Spoon into 2 prepared loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonful into hot fat and fry until rich brown.

title: hard jack candy
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients.
Add coloring at 250°.
Continue cooking to 300°.
Add flavoring after boiling to 300° and turn off heat.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Slice into strips and quickly cut with scissors into small pieces.
Place small pieces in powdered sugar as you cut them.

title: marinated zucchini salad
directions: Combine zucchini, green pepper, celery, onion and pimento in a medium bowl; set aside.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour marinade over vegetables; toss gently.
Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight. Serve with a slotted spoon.
Serve with hot buttered bread rolls. Makes 8 servings.

title: dirt
directions: Crush cookies in blender (use entire cookie).
Set aside.
Mix pudding with milk.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Then combine cream cheese mixture with pudding.
You can use a mixer on low speed.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: popettes
directions: Divide Corn Pops and nuts evenly in 2 pans.
Melt butter, syrup and sugar together.
Cook until bubbles.
Add baking soda; it will become foamy.
Pour over Corn Pops mixture and stir.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool on wax paper.

title: frozen punch
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes sugar and 3 cups water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze.
Thaw 6 to 8 hours.
I use this when it is thawed until slushy.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, green beans, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: tangy minute steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over minute steak and cook in oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: olive chili dunk
directions: Drain olives; set some aside for garnish.
Mix remaining olives with other ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve in chilled bowl.
Set out bread sticks, celery sticks and crisp raw vegetables for dunking.

title: recipe for life
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add Tears of Joy, Sorrow and Sympathy for Others.
Fold in cups of Prayer and Faith to lighten other ingredients and raise the texture to great heights of living. After pouring all this into your family, bake well with the heat of Human Kindness.
Serve everyone with a smile.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale. Chill. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: chinese salad
directions: Mix together rice vinegar, sugar, oil and Accent.
Add to other ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: super summer salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well. Refrigerate until ready to eat.
Serves 4.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Freeze.
Serve 1/3 frozen mixture to half (7-Up) in glass.

title: old fashioned vanilla tea cakes
directions: Place the sugar and vanilla bean in a tightly closed container and set aside for 1 week.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Gradually add lemon juice and pie filling into Jell-O. Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.

title: mandarin orange cake 1
directions: Use two round pans or oblong pan, grease and flour.
Mix cake according to directions and add mandarin oranges.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until done.
Let it cool completely.
Combine dry pudding mix with the pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and mix well. Top or layer and top the cake with the Cool Whip topping.
Keep cake in the refrigerator.

title: wild bill's hillbilly chili
directions: Start sauce in a large pot. Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, chili powder and chili beans. Cook on low. Small dice bell pepper, onion, chili peppers, tomatoes and garlic.
Mix together and saute in pan with butter until almost clear, but not brown.
Drain and add to sauce. Brown ground beef in a large pan. Drain real good. Add to sauce.
Cook for 45 minutes on low. Stir frequently.
Add brown sugar.
Cook another 20 minutes and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Add all ingredients, except the cheese whiz, and cover with water.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Spoon in jar of cheez whiz.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir well all ingredients. Add 1 medium container of Cool Whip; stir and let refrigerate.

title: egg casserole(serves 6)
directions: Mix ingredients; bake in casserole 1 hour at 350°, uncovered. You can make casserole up the night before by refrigerating and covering until baking time.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave.
Brown ground beef. Drain.
Add chili peppers and mushroom soup.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: warm beet salad
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Add peppers, cucumber and onion.
Cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Arrange beets on 4 individual plates and drizzle with vegetable mixture.
Serve warm.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix the sugar, flour and salt; set aside.
Bring to a boil the water, shortening, oleo and cocoa.
Add this to the sugar, flour and salt along with the eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Bake on a cookie sheet pan until done.

title: bean salad
directions: Chop onions and pepper.
Add all ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight.

title: rhubarb dump cake
directions: Put rhubarb in 9 inch x 13 inch glass pan.
Sprinkle sugar and jello over rhubarb.
Add water. Sprinkle cake mix over top. Add melted oleo.
Nuts are optional on top.
Do not mix or stir. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: steak in pepper cream
directions: Cook steaks in skillet sprinkled with salt until brown. Combine peppercorns, water and steak sauce in hot skillet.
Cook over medium heat, loosening browned food particles.
Stir in whipping cream and black pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 3 to 4 minutes to slightly thicken.
Add steak.
Simmer 5 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.
Stir occasionally.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl; add sugar, oil and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple. Add dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pan; turn out on rack to cool completely.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs in bowl, then add all other ingredients.
Pour into lasagna pan or casserole and bake for 1 hour at 325° or until corn pudding thickens.

title: almond cheese dip
directions: Combine ingredients and bake on party rye until golden.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together lard, flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in 7-Up.
Roll out for pie.
Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.

title: fruit on picks
directions: Dip banana slices in orange juice.
Roll in coconut.
Place fruit on 10-inch wooden skewer, alternating cherries, pineapple chunks, grapes and banana slices until skewers are filled.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken. Debone and put in bottom of pan.
Mix soup with broth.
Pour over chicken; don't stir.
Mix flour, milk and oleo; pour over other ingredients.
Don't stir.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown in skillet the ground beef, bacon and onion; drain. Make sauce and add to ground beef, bacon and onion.
Mix together meat sauce and beans.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.
Last hour, top with 1/2 pound bacon.

title: beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in saucepan.
When hot, add onions, garlic and parsley.
Mix and cook for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Add beef and thyme; mix well.
Continue cooking for 5 to 6 minutes over medium heat.
Stir occasionally and season. Add tomatoes and tomato paste; cook 4 to 5 minutes over low heat.

title: beet relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat through.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Seal.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes to complete seal.
Yields 3 to 4 pints.

title: mom's white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat 9 to 10 minutes to soft ball stage, 238°.
Remove from heat and allow to stand until candy reaches 110°, about 1 hour.
Add vanilla after the 1 hour.
Beat until fudge loses its gloss and holds its shape. Quickly stir in walnuts.
Put in a greased pan and flatten.

title: boarding house rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Put Crisco into milk and melt. Add sugar to milk. Add yeast mix to the milk mix. Add flour and salt and stir together. Knead to get all the flour mixed in. Brush with soft margarine and let rise about 2 hours in warm kitchen. Punch down, roll out and cut with biscuit cutter and form into Parker House style rolls, butter each roll before putting into pan. Let rise 2 hours again. Bake at 450° on top rack for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: temptation cake
directions: Mix ingredients and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: onion crescent crunch sticks
directions: Mix eggs, margarine, flour, garlic, parsley and onion salt in flat dish.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles (pinch together perforations for triangles).
Cut each rectangle into 8 strips. Crush onion rings in flat bowl.
Dip strips in egg mixture and then in crushed onion rings.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes

title: baklava
directions: Prepare a Box of Brownies According to the Box Recipe.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oil and sugar and mix well.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda and blend until well blended. Add oatmeal and stir until well mixed.
Add peanut butter and chocolate chips and mix well.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: chili con carne pie
directions: Saute onion, garlic and beef.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese and cornbread topping.

title: orange pop jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water in large bowl.
Add cooled pop; chill until slightly jelled.
Beat in Cool Whip; stir in orange slices.
Top with marshmallows.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 large bowls.

title: fruit punch for children
directions: Pour tea over sugar.
Add to this orange and lemon juice.
Put fairly large amount of ice.
Let stand awhile.
Just before serving, add 2 small bottles (12 ounce) ginger ale.
Decorate with slices of orange and sprigs of mint.
Makes 2 1/2 pints.

title: firehouse chili
directions: *The Fire Chief assured me 1/4 cup is correct.

title: mother's corn cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on hot greased griddle. Serve with syrup.

title: hot oyster dip
directions: Simmer all ingredients in a saucepan.
In another large, heavy saucepan mix 2 cans celery soup and two 8 ounce cartons sour cream (soup is undiluted).
Heat slowly.
Lift oysters and seasonings out of pan, using slotted spoon and stir into soup mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve in chafing dish with toast points.
This recipe doubles or triples well.

title: blueberry dream pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and beat until creamy.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Brush egg yolk on crust and bake in a 375° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool.
To cream cheese mixture stir in 3/4 cup blueberry pie filling.
Dig a well in center of pie and place remaining blueberry filling in well.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy and milk.
Beat eggs and sugar; add chocolate milk. Mix together.
Put in your electric cream churn.

title: e.z. turkey casserole
directions: Place cooked noodles in an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Spread turkey over noodles.
Add broth and mushrooms.
Sprinkle on onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: easy turkey oven meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch metal pan.
Chop bread into fine crumbs (approximately 1 cup).
Grate onion to measure 1 tablespoon.
Add to bread crumbs, along with turkey, spinach, salt, pepper and egg.
Shape into 16 meatballs.
Bake for 25 minutes, turning as they brown.
When meatballs are done, add to your own favorite tomato sauce recipe or any favorite ready made tomato sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes or more to blend flavors. Serve over spaghetti or rice.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: chicken breasts with smoked sausage
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken; brown well and drain fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: steamed sponge pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and ginger.
Add all but the 2 tablespoons of dry ingredients alternately with milk; mix gently.
Mix the remaining ingredients with the dried fruit and fold into the batter.
Pour batter into well-greased 1 1/2-quart mold.
Cover with lid or foil.
Set on rack in pan of boiling water with water extended 2/3 of the way up.
Steam for 1 1/2 hours, replenishing water as needed.
Unmold and serve warm with hard sauce.

title: sweet potato casserole(club member: john waters)
directions: Beat with mixer until smooth. Pour into dish.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas; add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half; remove seeds and place in baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and spoon into peppers. Cover and microwave on High 10 minutes.

title: pecan  poppy loaf
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Stir in pecans and poppy seed.
Makes about 3 medium size loaves.
Spray aluminum loaf pans with Baker's Joy.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with softened cream cheese.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Mix onion, celery, oleo, salt and pepper. Pour water carefully over mixture.
Sprinkle with rice.
Mix soup together with Miracle Whip and milk.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°, covered.
Uncover and sprinkle with paprika and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: mints
directions: Mix together and add food color and flavoring of any flavor you like.
Cream it together and put in sugared molds and chill. Pop out and sprinkle with sugar.

title: banana pudding
directions: Fold, don't beat, the first four ingredients together.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Sprinkle crumbled wafers on top.

title: onion soup pork chop
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown pork chops in skillet over medium heat.
In mixing bowl, combine soup mix and rice.
Mix together and spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay browned chops on top of rice; pour water over the chops.
Cover dish tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour or until internal temperature of pork chops has reached 160°.

title: chinese rice
directions: Saute onion and butter; set aside.
Lightly scramble eggs in frying pan.
Add rice, onion, water and soy sauce; fry one or more minutes.
Serve hot.

title: date cookies
directions: Combine butter, salt
and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs and
mix well.
Sift flour with soda and add
to creamed
mixture.
Alternate
with
milk,
mixing thoroughly.
Add dates and
pecans.
Stir
in
well.
Drop
by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten cookies with damp over the bottom
of a glass.
Sprinkle each cookie with sugar. Bake in 375° preheated oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: ladyfingers dessert
directions: Arrange Ladyfingers in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: marshmallow dessert
directions: Mix pineapple in whipped cream.
Add grated cheese and marshmallows.
Mix well and refrigerate, 2 to 3 hours.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs with mixer.
Add sugar, oil, milk and vanilla to eggs; mix well.
Mix flour, soda and poppy seed; add to prepared mixture.
Pour into floured and greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 60 minutes, or until done.
Use 2 loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat the eggs.
Stir in milk and oil.
Add dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonful on hot, ungreased griddle.
Cook until bubbles appear on top.
Turn and cook on other side.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: peanut butter and fruit bars
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine honey and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil. Continue cooking and stirring one minute longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, raisins and mixed fruit until combined.
Add rice cereal and mix until cereal is coated.
Press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; cool.
Cut into 2 1/4 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes 32 bars.

title: beef with oyster sauce in green paradise
directions: In large bowl, mix the wine, soy sauce, sesame oil and cornstarch.
Add steak slices and toss with a large spoon to coat them thoroughly.
Cook at once or marinate 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut broccoli and pour 2 quarts of water into a 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil, add 1 teaspoon salt, return to boil after adding broccoli. Let rest, uncovered, 2 minutes.
Remove to large bowl.
In saucepan or wok, heat 2 tablespoons oil to smoke stage and pour over broccoli immediately.
Add 1 tablespoon oyster sauce, mix well. Arrange broccoli on bottom of a plate.
Stir-fry steak in 3 tablespoons oil in wok 2 minutes (no pink).
Add 1 tablespoon oyster sauce and mix well.
Add to top of broccoli and serve at once.

title: stove top casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off the fat.
Spread onions, vegetables and potatoes over hamburger.
Top with soup and water. Cover and cook over medium heat 20 to 30 minutes, stirring often. Serves 4.
Good for a quick dinner.

title: inside outside chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Ice when cooled.

title: mock hollandaise
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill at least 1/2 hour. Good dip for artichokes, asparagus, tomatoes, carrots, etc.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Add other ingredients together in crock-pot or double boiler.
Add sausage and cook on low temperature for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until cheeses are melted.
Serve over chips.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: mother's fruitcake
directions: Butter and flour baking pan (tube, loaf or 16 ounce size cans from corn, peas, etc., washed).
Fill with batter until 1/2 to 3/4 full after combining all ingredients.
Sift flour and soda.
In a larger bowl, combine all other ingredients, then fold in dry ingredients.
Bake at 300° for about 1 to 2 hours depending on size and shape of pan used.
Enjoy!

title: butter krunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch and peanut butter in microwave about 3 minutes.
Mix vanilla, then cornflakes, thoroughly coating them. Drop on cookie sheet, then refrigerate.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain. Combine all other ingredients in large pot.
Add cucumbers to vinegar mixture and heat to boiling.
Put in jars.
Seal while hot. (Water bath 15 minutes, optional.)
Yield:
About 6 pints.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add egg, butter and chopped nuts. Stir well and add cherries.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan for 45 minutes at 325° until done.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Steam broccoli until partially cooked.
Cool.
Drain.
Press dry.
Beat eggs and milk until frothy.
Thoroughly mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in egg mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in broccoli, cheese and onion. Spoon into baking pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until set and lightly brown at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Before you go to bed, grease a 10 inch bundt pan and add frozen rolls; sprinkle with brown sugar, and pudding powder, and cinnamon. Pour melted butter over and cover with a clean damp cloth. Let stand at room temperature. The next morning, preheat oven to 350° and bake about 25 minutes. Let set for 5 minutes before serving.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with 3 cups water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and cook, stirring constantly for 5 minutes. Cool (very important to cool completely).
Whip 1 package Dream Whip.
Add to cooled Jell-O mixture.
Add 1 can mandarin oranges (drained).
You can leave whole or cut in half.

title: homemade onion rings
directions: Use any medium size pot (use little burner).

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Place blueberries in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, margarine, milk and baking powder.
Pour batter over berries.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Pour over batter.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over all. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: goulash(aka nuts and bolts)
directions: Heat oven to 250°. Place butter in 9 x 13 pan and put in oven until butter melts. Add Worcestershire and salts to butter. Add remaining ingredients, stirring to coat evenly. Return to oven and bake for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool and store in a tightly covered container.

title: beth's creamy chicken bake
directions: Remove skin off of
chicken.
Arrange in a 2 to 3 quart baking dish.
Put a
slice of cheese on each piece of chicken. Stir together soup
and	wine.
Pour on the chicken.
Coarsely crush stuffing over
the	top.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Mix all together until smooth.
Beat 10 minutes.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, 1 1/4 cups sugar, lemon juice, lemon rind and salt.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to dry mixture.
Gradually add boiling water.
Heat to boiling over direct heat.
Boil gently for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Gradually beat in 6 tablespoons sugar.
Spread meringue over top of pie to touch all edges of crust.
Bake at 425° for 4 to 5 minutes.
Cool on a cake rack. Serve cold.

title: zesty chicken bake
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, in small bowl, combine soup, brown sugar, water, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce; set aside.
Spoon soup mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes more or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and margarine.
Cook for 2 minutes and 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper or lightly buttered sheet pan to cool. Yields 20 to 30 pieces.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix everything together and beat until thoroughly mixed. Preheat oven to 325°; grease and flour tube or Bundt pan; if nuts are used, sprinkle over bottom of pan; pour batter over nuts and bake 1 hour.
Cool; invert onto serving platter and prick top of cake with fork.
Top with Rum Glaze.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream together the Crisco and honey. Add the All-Bran, 100% bran cereal and boiling water. Blend in the eggs.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt. Add the ???.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes a large batch.
Store batter in refrigerator in jars until ready to bake.

title: pecan cinnamon rolls
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with PAM.
Place 20 biscuits into pan or whatever it takes to fill pan.
Mix sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Set-aside.
In saucepan, melt 1 stick margarine. Remove from heat, add sugar/nut mixture and 1 tablespoon water. Stir until mixed.
Spoon mixture over biscuits. Bake at 400° about 15 to 18 minutes.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Mix ingredients together and toss with pretzels.
Toss each hour until dry.
Keeps well in Ziploc bags.

title: margarita shrimp
directions: Heat oil in large heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp, onion and garlic and saute until shrimp turns pink (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat and add tequila; return to heat and bring to a boil, scraping up any browned bits.
Transfer to medium bowl and cool.
Toss shrimp with lime juice and salt.
Garnish with lime wedges and serve.

title: cool whip pies
directions: Mix lemon juice and condensed milk with spoon.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Put pie filling on top of pie as a topping. Refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: country fried apples
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Heat margarine or drippings in skillet.
Add apples; cover and steam to desired tenderness (can use a small amount of water if needed).
When apples are almost done, add sugar; continue to cook until apples are glazed and keep their shape.
Delicious.

title: pecos pasta
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Melt butter; add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Do not brown.
Add chilli, corn, seasoned salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked macaroni; top with cheese. Cover and heat on low for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter sweet treats
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll pieces of mixture into balls and place on wax paper.
Refrigerate one hour.

title: little man muffins
directions: Heat muffins as package label directs, sliced crosswise in half.
Spread 1 tablespoon cream cheese over cut side of bottom half of each muffin; cover with top half of muffin, cut side down. Place remaining cream cheese in small pastry bag fitted with star tip.
Make eyes and hair on each muffin top.
Attach raisins, cream-cheese eyes; press apples in muffin for hair, nose and mouth. Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt wanda's carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add remaining ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: five cup salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O in water, then dissolve cream cheese in Jell-O
and
hot water.
Add milk, pineapple and pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: german cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into ball.
Flatten into 10-inch pie plate.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-O in hot water. Fold in pineapple and strawberries. Add bananas. Pour half of mixture into square dish. Congeal. Spread top with layer of sour cream. Pour remaining mixture on top of sour cream and congeal. Serve on lettuce.

title: kraft caramel dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar, margarine and nuts.
Press into oblong pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake pizza crust on cookie sheet 5 to
minutes,
let cool. Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing
mix together; then stir mayonnaise and spread over pizza
crust.
Cut
vegetables up small
(Salad Shooter works great).
Layer	vegetables
on pizza crust and topping.	Sprinkle with cheese.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix together 2 sticks margarine, 2 tablespoons cocoa, vanilla, sugar, eggs, coconut, flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
As soon as cake is removed from oven, spread with marshmallow cream.
Now, melt remaining margarine; stir in other ingredients (milk, 3 1/2 tablespoons cocoa and confectioners sugar).
Spread over marshmallow cream.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Roll into balls.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: yummy party mix
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar.
Boil 2 minutes (good).
Pour over cereal mixture and mix.
Bake 8 minutes more.
Let cool.

title: crab dip
directions: Cut crab into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and spread on crackers.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Blend cornstarch with small amount of cold stock in a large saucepan.
Add the rest of the stock, mixing well, and then remaining ingredients except eggs.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until clear, stirring occasionally.
Slowly stir in eggs.
Season to taste.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Do not use mint or black gumdrops.
Cream together the sugars and shortening.
Add eggs then flour, which has been mixed with salt, soda and baking powder.
Next add vanilla then the coconut and quick oats.
Last, add the gumdrops.
Drop by spoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: easy does it chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Place chicken pieces between two sheets of wax paper.
Flatten pieces slightly with a meat mallet. Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper and drip a little lemon juice over each piece.
Dip chicken in egg, then bread crumbs to coat well on both sides.
Melt butter or margarine in large skillet over moderately high heat.
Fry chicken pieces until golden brown, about 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Do not overcook or chicken will become tough.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Add all ingredients and fold over and over. Put some cheese on top. Squeeze butter on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, put 2 cups all-bran and pour boiling water with oleo in it over the bran.
Add remaining 4 cups cereal, eggs and sugar; mix well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk, alternately, until all of both are used.
Cover and store in refrigerator up to
6 weeks.
Bake in muffin pan at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and press into a 9 X 12 pan.
Mix the remaining four ingredients together and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 300 for 1 hour.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: okra, fried
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add enough flour to coat. Fry in bacon drippings and cooking oil. Cook, covered and over low heat, stirring occasionally 10 or 15 minutes or until tender.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: In a saucepan, boil water.
Add salt.
Add grits slowly. Stir.
Cook 4 1/2 minutes or until thick.
Cut up cheese.
Add cheese, butter, milk and then beaten eggs.
Take off heat.

title: hot crab sandwich
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with mayonnaise; fold in crabmeat.
Split muffins.
Place a tomato slice on each split muffin, cover with 1 large spoonful of crab mixture.
Top each with generous sprinkling of grated cheese.	Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolk, nuts and pineapple. Fold in beaten egg whites. Spread between layers of 2 vanilla wafers. Chill for 4 hours; roll in whipped cream and then in coconut. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, onion, mayonnaise, celery, water chestnuts and cheese.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs, mixed with a little melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato rosti
directions: Peel potatoes and chop onions. Combine potatoes, onion and salt. Heat 2 skillets. Heat

butter until slightly brown. Add half of potato mixture to each skillet. Cook for about 8 minutes stirring once or twice. Add grated cheese and firmly press mixture. Cook, covered about 5 minutes until bottom is crispy. Turn over and cook 5 more minutes. Low to medium heat.

title: strawberries and cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour three 9-inch round cake pans. In large bowl, beat sugar, gelatin and butter until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beat well with each addition. Mix flour and baking powder, and beat alternately with milk into the sugar mixture. Fold in 1 tsp. vanilla and pureed strawberries. Divide equally into the three prepared cake pans. Bake for 25 minutes in preheated oven, or until toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes in pans, then remove from pans and cool completely.

title: shrimp mold
directions: This is best if made a day or 2 ahead.

title: custard with topping on the bottom
directions: In a large heatproof pitcher, beat the eggs.
Add granulated sugar and salt.
Slowly blend in the scalded milk and stir in the vanilla.
In the bottom of each custard cup, put a rounded tablespoon of dark brown sugar and pour the egg mixture in.
Set in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° until a knife comes out clean, about 1/2 hour.

title: watergate salad (no. 2)
directions: Mix pistachio pudding and Cool Whip and set aside.
Mix the last 4 ingredients well, then add to the pudding mixture and refrigerate.

title: italian quanti
directions: Add flour to suit.
Roll it thin; cut into strips and twist as you fry.
Lay out on paper towels to cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chocolate almond cream pie
directions: Melt candy bars until just melted (they should not be very hot).
Stir together the thawed Cool Whip very rapidly.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Slice and serve!

title: peach jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Stir in peach filling and nuts; mix well.
Congeal.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar; spread on top.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Saute beef and onion until lightly browned.
Add soup, 1 teaspoon of salt, water, pepper, corn, chili powder and green pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Place in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; set aside.
Combine cornbread, flour, sugar, remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and baking powder.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Spoon cornbread topping over meat mixture.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: chicken and green bean bake
directions: Cook frozen green beans for 2 to 3 minutes.
Save 1/2 cup liquid.
Pour drained beans in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish. Place cooked chicken on green beans.
Put 2 soups plus bean liquid and cheese (cut into cubes) in saucepan.
Cook until cheese is melted, stirring continually.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle mushrooms over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Combine ground beef, green pepper and onion in a large skillet; cook until meat is browned, stirring to crumble; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; spoon mixture into a lightly greased baking dish (10 x 6 x 2 inches) and bake uncovered at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Yield 4 to 6 servings.

title: upside-down cake(pineapple or peach)
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Drain pineapple (save juice).
Arrange pineapple slices with cherry halves in center on sugar mixture.
Add water to pineapple juice to make the water called for on cake recipe. Make cake batter.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: diet strawberry pie
directions: Mix the cornstarch in a little cold water. Add to boiling water and jello. Boil for 2 minutes. Let cool. Add Equal and pour in strawberries. Pour this mixture in crust and chill. Top with Cool Whip.

title: gram's french cream cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in round pans (do not grease pans) for 35 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Split layers and put cream between layers.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Cover top and sides with cream.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook sauces together. Mix well with hamburger and onion. Add seasonings to your taste!

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend together the first 5 ingredients.
Wrap 1 teaspoon around each of the 24 olives.
Cover completely.
Arrange on ungreased baking sheet.
Refrigerate.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: flounder au gratin with mushrooms
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper and arrange in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Melt butter; add and blend lemon juice, then add mushrooms and saute over low heat 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in flour, then add cream gradually and simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.
Simmer 10 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Add sherry and pinch of salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over fish and sprinkle with cheese, then bread crumbs and a dash of paprika.
Bake 20 minutes at 450° or until fish is no longer transparent and flakes easily and top is nicely browned.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground meat with taco seasoning and drain.
Add beans to meat and heat until beans are warm.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread sour cream over top of mixture.
Shred lettuce and add on top.
Layer over with chopped tomatoes and onions.
Put taco sauce over top and add grated cheese.
Top with chips.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Make a well in center of flour and pour milk in well. Stir until dough cleans the bowl (not over half a minute).
Knead dough 1/2 minute.
Pat dough out on a floured surface to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter and bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: harvard beets
directions: About 20 minutes before serving, drain beets, reserving 1/2 cup of beet liquid.

title: bee sting cake
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and water. Stir over moderate heat until mixture simmers and sugar dissolves.
Pour half syrup mixture into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Sprinkle with nuts. Mix cake according to package.
Pour half of batter in each pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool 5 minutes and remove.
Scrape left topping onto cakes.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: spinach rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in water
until moisture is taken up.
Add the milk to rice and cook until well taken up.
Stir in cheese until blended.
In a quart baking dish that
has
been
buttered,
put a layer of rice, then spinach.
Repeat layers.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in hot 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: scallops and snow peas
directions: In a large skillet, melt 1/4 cup butter, saute shallots until golden.
Add pea pods and scallions.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Remove to heated platter.
To same skillet, add sea scallops, cut into quarters.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes until done.
Do not overcook. Remove with slotted spoon and place over vegetables on platter.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients and add dry ingredients.
Stir carefully. Turn batter into two greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then turn out onto cooling racks.
Ice with any desired icing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and place in buttered casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take out of refrigerator one hour ahead.
Put crumbs or croutons on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 1 large and 1 small casserole.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cut corn off the cob.
Mix together corn, soup, bouillon, pepper and 1/3 of Durkee onions.
Add 1/2 can water.
Put into 1 to 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cover loosely with foil.
Keeps down overbrowning of onions.

title: new orleans barbecued shrimp
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven.
Except for the shrimp, add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the sauce boils.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 8 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, uncovered, at least 30 minutes.
About 20 minutes before serving, add shrimp and cook over medium heat to 6 to 8 minutes until shrimp turn pink.
Bake 10 minutes in a preheated 450° oven. Ladle shrimp and sauce into bowls and serve with plenty of crusty French bread for dipping into the sauce.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add onion, seasonings and flour; stir well.
Add
rest
of
ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally. May cook slowly several hours.

title: small family rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt and 1/2 flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add shortening.
Beat in remaining flour; stir until smooth.
Let rise in a warm place until double in size or set in pan of hot water about 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: honey mustard chicken wings with sesame seed
directions: Marinate the chicken pieces for at least 2 hours or overnight. Cook when guests arrive.
If using chicken wings, separate them at the joints into 3 sections.
Discard tips or save for stock. Place chicken in shallow dish.
In a 1-cup glass measure, combine honey, soy sauce and mustard.
Stir to blend well.
Cook on High 1 minute.
Brush chicken wings with honey mixture.
Roll wings in sesame seed to coat lightly.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Arrange on a shallow 9-inch plate, like spokes on a wheel, with thickest portion facing outside of dish.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Place cream cheese, cottage cheese and mayonnaise in bowl. Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Refrigerate until served.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: carol's pecan pie
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients then add the next 5 and mix well.
Pour into the shell, decorate with the remaining nuts and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 55 minutes.
(You may want to place the pie in the lower 1/2 of the oven to keep the top from browning before the custard is properly set.)
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and press in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Take powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and mix together.
Spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 300° until golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: layered hot fruit salad
directions: Mix together 1 can applesauce and 1 can cranberry sauce; put 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix 4 medium sliced bananas into other fruit; place all on top of sauce mixture. Top with other 1/2 of sauces mix. Dot with butter and sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If you have questions, call Judy.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a
boil, then cover and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove lid and cook until soft, firm ball stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup slowly over beaten egg whites.
Continue beating.
Add vanilla and beat until it loses gloss.
Add nuts last, if desired. Spoon out quickly on wax paper.

title: martha dean's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs 5 to 8 minutes; add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add Milnot.
Pour mixture into freezer can.
Add milk to fill line.

title: mother's green tomato pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with rich pastry.
Slice tomatoes thin and mound slightly in center.
Sugar mixture should be added gradually between layer of tomatoes.
Add lemon juice, allspice and butter on top.
Add top crust and bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° when pie starts to bubble and continue baking until filling has thickened and tomatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and cool.
Enjoy with ice cream.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onion and carrots in butter.
Add to a soup pot the onion, carrots, potatoes, salt, chicken broth and water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add parsley, juice from clams, milk and wine.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add clams.
Simmer 5 more minutes and serve.

title: sausage casserole 1
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Saute onion and celery.
Simmer rice in water for 15 minutes.
Add soup mix and simmer 15 minutes, until tender.
Mix all together, put into greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs or almonds.
(I put in 2 dishes and freeze one.)
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fluff
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and line 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: spicy beef
directions: Brown ground beef without oil until the pink is gone.
Place in a mixing bowl.
Put in ground kha, coriander seed powder and garlic powder.
Mix well, then let cool for 5 minutes.
Season the beef with fish sauce, salt, lime juice, rice powder, chili powder and chopped red onion.
Then add mint leaves, green onion and sprig coriander; mix well.

title: all-in-one-coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given and mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Very good.
Easy, just mix and cook.

title: bob's fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and food coloring.
Stir until blended well.
Place peaches in baked pie crust and pour mixture over them.
Top with whipped cream before serving, if desired.

title: fruit bars
directions: Grease 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Cover bottom with pecans.
Make batter of other ingredients except pineapple and cherries; pour batter over pecans and press it in with dampened hands.
Cut fruit and press in slightly to mix evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off burner.
Add marshmallow cream and stir until melted.
Add chocolate morsels, stir until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 3 pounds of fudge.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt cheese in soup.
Pour over uncooked vegetables in a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin with mixer.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Pour into ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with icing.

title: mom mom's applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly, add egg and beat well. Blend in applesauce.
Sift together, flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice, ground cloves and nutmeg. Blend creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in raisins and walnuts. Bake in moderate oven (350°).

title: rocky road candy
directions: Place chocolate chips, condensed milk and margarine in top of a double boiler.
Cook over medium heat until chocolate and margarine are melted.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper. Drop spoonfuls of candy on paper.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: christmas custard
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat cream over low heat until bubbles (stir constantly); form on edge of pan.
Beat yolks and sugar together until thick and yellow (3 minutes).
Beating constantly, pour cream in steady steam into egg yolks; add vanilla.
Pour into custard cups.
Place cups into baking pan with 1/2 to 1-inch boiling water lining bottom of pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Remove cups; cool.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar. Place under broiler (close) and cook until sugar turns golden brown.
Refrigerate before serving.
Yummy!
Top will be crisp.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: In a sprayed 1 1/2 qt. casserole, combine all the ingredients except the cheese.
Sprinkle the cheese on top and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serves:

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and remove potato from inside of skins, leaving skins intact to re-stuff later.
Mash the potatoes with butter and milk.
Add sour cream, onion, chives, salt and pepper.
Mix ingredients well.
Stuff the potato skins and cover with grated cheese and cubed cheese.
Bake in moderate oven until cheese is melted and golden brown.

title: q v c cheese-vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and stir to dissolve flour.
Add milk; bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Next, add cheese and stir until melted.
Then add mustard, vegetables and 1 to 2 cups water (to desired thickness).
Let set 30 minutes.

title: louisiana caramel pralines
directions: Note:
Make on cold crisp days, low humidity.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake on hot griddle.
Makes eight 4-inch pancakes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cherries.
After mixing, sprinkle more coconut on top and pour cherry juice over top and place cherries on top.

title: onion dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor and blend for 5 minutes. Dressing can be used on fruit or vegetable salad and is good on baked potato.

title: john machetti
directions: Boil noodles 5 minutes and drain.
Saute meat and onions, drain.
Add tomato sauce and soup.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and cover with grated cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: grand marnier french toast
directions: Slice bread 1 1/2-inches thick.
Arrange slices in plastic or glass container (flat works best).
Mix next five ingredients and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: ground meat and noodle casserole
directions: Put your first 4 ingredients in skillet and saute.
Brown your ground beef and mix together.
Put two cups of cooked noodles, 1 can of mixed vegetables and 1 can of cream of mushroom soup.
Put your first five ingredients in casserole dish.
Add your noodles, vegetable mix and soups.
Add slices of cheese on top.
Bake around 300° for 30 minutes.

title: cream filled chocolate cookie ice cream pie
directions: Mix crushed cookies with melted butter.
Press into the bottom of a 12-inch pie taker.

title: green stuffed peppers
directions: Boil peppers 20 to 30 minutes.
Brown meat; drain grease.
Add tomatoes, 1/2 of tomato sauce, all seasonings and chopped onion to meat.
Add rice to meat.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Place green peppers in a baking dish.
Top with remaining tomato sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake butter cake mix following package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: In small bowl, beat first four ingredients on low speed until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Press 1/3 of dough into bottom of pan; keep remaining dough in refrigerator.
Bake bottom crust 8 minutes; cool.
Turn oven up to 475°.
Then mix the next eight ingredients at medium speed until blended, then beat on high speed for 5 minutes.
Press 2/3 dough on sides of pan within 1-inch of top.
Pour filling into pan.
Bake at 475° for 12 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300° and continue baking for 50 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave inside for 30 more minutes.
Cool out of oven for 30 more minutes, then refrigerate.

title: grandma's banana bread
directions: Grease and flour 1 large or 2 small loaf bread pan(s).
Melt margarine.

title: johnny mascetti casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Brown hamburger.
Place everything in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking
dish.
Combine
corn flakes with 1/4 cup butter and top casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt butter. Add cream, egg, cheese and all other ingredients. Add cooked noodles last.
Stir well and serve at once.

title: pumpkin fluff
directions: Mix together pumpkin, spice and milk until well blended.
Add pudding mix and beat by hand 2 minutes.
Fold in cool whip. Refrigerate.
Serves:

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with foil and grease foil.
In a 3-quart microwave bowl, stir sugar, syrup and peanut butter. Microwave at High, stirring 2 times during 3 1/2 to 4 minutes, or until mixture is smooth and sugar is dissolved.
Add cereal.
Stir to coat well.
Press evenly into prepared pan.
Cool.
Remove from pan, cut into squares and store in tightly covered container. Makes 4 dozen.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread out sugar cookie dough in 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread on top of crust.
Add on top any fruit combination.
Glaze.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and salt in pan.
Beat until butter melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Add yeast, stir to dissolve.
Add flour into milk mixture and stir to blend well.
Cover and let rise 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls and dip in melted margarine or butter.
Lay balls in Bundt pan.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add rice cereal and mix with hands. Form into small balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls in while chocolate is warm.
Place on waxed paper to harden.

title: jubilee jumbles cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars and eggs.
Stir in milk, vanilla, sifted flour, soda and salt.
Stir in gradually.
Chill for 1 hour.
Drop with tablespoon 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: crispy chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: In shallow dish, dip chicken into egg; coat with seasoned crumbs.
In skillet on medium heat, add oil.
Cook chicken 15 minutes or until browned on both sides and no longer pink.
Remove and keep warm.
Pour off fat.
In skillet over low heat, combine soup, milk and water.
Heat through, stirring.
Serve over chicken with rice.
Serves 4.

title: hashed brown potato casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Place in buttered 8 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with onion rings.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chilli beans
directions: Brown ground beef and beef stew.
Combine with remaining ingredients and simmer until beef is tender.

title: rhubarb-strawberry pie
directions: In large bowl, mix fruit, sugar, eggs and crackers together. Put in unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Put top crust on. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: heavenly fruit pie
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix milk with lemon juice and fold in whipped topping.
Add fruit; pour into 2 pie shells.
Chill for 2 or 3 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into an oiled 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Cream cheese and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Spread over crust.
Spoon glaze over creamed mixture.
Top with assorted bite-sized fresh fruit in season.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: scalloped chicken casserole
directions: In bowl, combine soup, milk and cheese.
Add chicken, macaroni and eggs.
Stir in 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Let set in refrigerator awhile for best results.
Toss bread crumbs with remaining margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for
1 hour or until bubbly and golden brown.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Place 15 whole graham crackers on bottom.
Mix French vanilla instant pudding with 3 cups cold milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Spoon half of mixture over crackers.
Place 15 more graham crackers over top.
Place other half over top.
Add another layer of 15 graham crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring spiced vinegar to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions. Bring to boiling point.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: pecan caramel popcorn
directions: Mix popcorn and nuts in large baking pan.
In a saucepan, combine butter, sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and nuts.
Stir well.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: korean beef
directions: Mix all ingredients except beef.
Add beef and let marinade for at least one hour.
Barbecue or broil.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix everything together in casserole.
Microwave on High for about 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda in a bowl.
Cream Crisco, sugar, almond and vanilla, then add egg yolks, one at a time.
Alternate adding flour and buttermilk.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: italian spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti. Chop tomatoes, green peppers and onion. Toss everything together and chill at least 12 hours.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind first 5 ingredients and drain.
