Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse well and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to a full boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Pack into hot jars.
Adjust lids. Process in hot water bath canner 10 minutes.

title: salmon stew
directions: Cook onion in oleo until tender, not browned.
Add salmon. Cook 1 minute.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes uncovered.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Good served with corn bread.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour and soda.
Add flour alternately
with
sour cream. Stir in 5 flavorings well.
Pour into large
greased tube pan. Bake
at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do
not
open
door during baking.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in a blender a few at a time until very fine. Mix pudding according to package directions.
Beat cream cheese with milk.
Fold pudding, cream cheese and Cool Whip together. Layer the Oreos and creamed mixture in a new, plastic flowerpot, ending with Oreos on top to look like dirt.
Put a plastic flower in the middle and gummy worms candy around flower.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine margarine, 1 cup flour and confectioners sugar; mix well!
Press mixture into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (not longer).
While this is baking, combine beaten eggs, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Mix baking powder and flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Combine well.
Spread on hot baked layer and bake again for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chocolate chip date torte
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix dates, boiling water and soda.
Cool.
Cream oleo; add sugar and beaten eggs.
Add flour mixture alternately with date mixture.
Blend well.
Add vanilla. Put mixture in a large 9 x 13-inch loaf pan, greased.
Sprinkle top with chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Gently shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meatballs and drain fat.

title: turnip slaw
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients, except turnips.
Pour over turnips and toss well to coat.
Refrigerate several hours for flavors to blend.
Yields 4 servings.

title: orange cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients (except pecans); mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each with a pecan half.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until brown. Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute; remove to rack.

title: japanese fruit pies(makes 3)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 3 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust edges are golden brown.

title: cranberry-apple salad
directions: Mix well and put in greased 9 x 12-inch dish (add 1/4 to 1/2 cup water depending on how dry the apples appear.
If using frozen apples, don't add water.)

title: country bumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except pudding mix until well blended. Then add pudding mix.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 well-greased loaf pans at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg. Mix well.
Add apples, nuts and spices.
Mix and sift soda, salt and flour and add.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold, with or without ice cream, sauce or whipped cream.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if using glass).
Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch dish in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over oleo; pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.

title: beau monde veggie dip
directions: Mix all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or as long as possible.

title: sausage and more
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces or form bulk sausage into small balls.
Fry until well done; drain, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings.
Arrange layers of potatoes, apples and sausage in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine sugar, flour, and salt. Blend with water.
Pour over layer.
Drizzle drippings over all. Cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples and potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak across grain into thin strips, 1/8-inch thick. Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add meat.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.

title: peach dessert
directions: Stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder.
Combine egg, milk and melted margarine.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well. Spread into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Drain peaches and reserve 1/3 cup liquid.
Chop peaches and sprinkle atop batter.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, sausage and mushrooms.
In another pan cook noodles by directions.
Drain and add grated cheese while noodles and sausage are hot.
Add undiluted soup and corn last.

title: beef tips on rice
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a plastic bag. Shake to mix.
Place beef cubes in bag and shake well.
Heat oil in Dutch oven; add beef and cook until browned.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water; add to beef mixture.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger mozzarella casserole(canadian recipe)
directions: Gently mix beef with salt and pepper.
Shape into 8 patties about 1/2-inch thick.
Coat each with flour, dip in eggs and coat with bread crumbs.
Brown on both sides in skillet in oil. Arrange in single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place Mozzarella slice on each patty.
Put mushroom slices on top of cheese-covered patty.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until sauce is bubbly and cheese has melted, probably 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add tomato paste, water and spices.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, grated cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook shells in boiling water as directed.
Rinse in cold water.
Drain.

title: hearty beef 'n potato casserole
directions: Place Tater Tots in casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Place ground beef on top of potatoes.
Add broccoli, 1/2 can French fried onions and chopped tomato.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese, garlic powder and pepper.
Pour over beef mixture. Bake covered 20 minutes at 400°.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded cheese and the remaining 1/2 can of onions.
Bake uncovered 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: pork loin
directions: Salt and pepper loin. Cover with Kitchen Bouquet (this is the brand name for a basting mixture). Cook indirectly with lid closed. Combine all ingredients. Heat to boiling. Brush sauce on within 1 to 2 hours before ready. Baste until ready.

title: layer fruit cake
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar and cream. Beat eggs separately. Add yolks. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk. Add coconut, nuts and raisins which have been rolled in flour. Add remainder of eggs. Bake in 4 layers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter. Bring to a boil.
Stir frequently so peanuts don't burn or stick.
Pour over powdered sugar in large bowl.
Flatten out on butter cookie sheet.
Cool and cut into desired pieces.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; pat dry and prick with a fork.
Bake in a 425° oven for 40 to 60 minutes until tender.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Gently scoop out potato, leaving a thin shell.
Place potato pulp in small bowl.
Beat or mash pulp.
Add sour cream dip, Cheddar cheese, zucchini, carrot, salt and pepper.
Beat until smooth. If necessary, add 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.
Spoon potato mixture into potato shells.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Drain all canned veggies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash for 5 minutes; drain and chop.
Add remaining ingredients, except stuffing mix and margarine.
Mix stuffing and margarine together.
Layer half the squash mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with half the stuffing and margarine mixture. Repeat layers again.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion.
Cook until brown.
Add beans and tomato sauce and stir well.
Then add the remaining ingredients, adding flour last.
Stir well and remove from heat.

title: filet giovanni
directions: Sprinkle a well-seasoned cast-iron skillet with salt and pepper, then heat until a drop of water sizzles on it.
Add the steaks to the hot skillet and cook over medium-high heat for about 3 minutes per side or until desired degree of doneness.
Remove steaks from pan.

title: snow crop spread
directions: Mix deviled ham and onion.
Mound on a plate and frost with mixture of cream cheese, mustard and sour cream.

title: blueberry muffins(old fashioned scratch blueberry muffins with a hint of orange)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line muffin pan with paper cups or grease 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine rolled oats and orange juice; stir well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt, soda, oil and egg.
Mix well.
Stir in blueberries.

title: 24 hour omelet
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add dash of cayenne.
Place bread cubes in 9 X 13 dish pan and spread with sausage.
Add green chile.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard together.
Pour over bread and meat.
Top with cheese.
Cover with foil and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Bake covered for 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.
Let sit for 15 - 25 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: vanilla kranse(rings)
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg and vanilla together and add the flour. Force through a cookie press; cut into strips and form into rings.
Bake at 375°.

title: caramel-nut roll
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Cook, stirring constantly, to 245° on candy thermometer.
Stir in butter.
Add milk slowly so mixture continues to boil and cook again to 245°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pour into well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan until firm.
Spread walnuts on buttered waxed paper the size of pan. Turn candy (when cool) out on top of walnuts and press them in the candy.
Roll as a jelly roll.
Cut in sections and wrap in plastic wrap or waxed paper.
Slice to serve.

title: egg noodles
directions: Combine beaten eggs, water and salt.
Beat well; add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead well on a floured board.
Roll out very thin.
Let dry 1 hour.
Cut into narrow strips.
Drop into boiling broth (chicken or beef).
Boil about 5 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spread popcorn out in a 17 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Chop onion and pepper.
Brown ground beef.
Add onion and pepper to beef.
When these 3 are cooked, add cooked egg noodles, peas and tomato soup. Salt to taste.
Put ingredients in baking dish.
Cover with sliced cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cookie surprise
directions: Take 2 cookies, place Cool Whip on back of one cookie.
Then sprinkle candy sprinkles on the Cool Whip; place the other cookie on top.
Then on top of the cookie, place a dot of Cool Whip on each left and right side of the cookie and place an M&M's for the eyes, the same for the nose and mouth and there you have a cookie surprise.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, stir in salsa, Miracle Whip, and chili powder.
Layer half meat mixture, chips, and cheese in casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato, if desired.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Press into pan, forming loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Place mini cupcake liners on a cookie sheet.
Melt together margarine, chocolate and 3/4 cup peanut butter.
In another pan, melt 3/4 cup peanut butter.

title: hot and spicy cashew chicken
directions: In large frypan or wok heat cooking oil.
Add chicken and saute until chicken is evenly browned.
Add vegetable and saute for 3 minutes.
Add soy sauce and red pepper to taste.
Cook 1 minute.
Add salted cashews.
Mix well, cook 2 minutes until well heated.
Serve immediately over fried or white rice.

title: pillow potato biscuits
directions: Combine potato flakes, sugar, butter and hot water; mix well. Add cold water and biscuit mix.
Add a little more cold water to make
a
soft
dough.
Turn
out
on
lightly floured surface; knead
about
10 times.
Roll dough; cut with cutter or jar lid. Put
on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush with milk. Bake at 450° about 13 minutes.

title: hearty hot pecan spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the pecans.
Spread into an 8-inch flat casserole dish.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with corn chips, crackers or celery sticks.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, cocoa and Milnot.
Let boil one minute, then add quick cooking oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Drop on wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Mix lemon juice, soy sauce and garlic powder together.
Wash chicken, place chicken in the mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Grill on an open grill or indoor grill until done.
Serve over a bed of salad greens with your favorite salad dressing.

title: frosty strawberry squares(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: velvet cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar until very smooth and light.
Add unbeaten eggs one at a time.
Sift flour before measuring, then sift all dry ingredients together several times.
Add dry ingredients to the creamed mixture, alternating with the milk, mixing well.
Last, add desired flavoring.
This cake may be made either by hand beating or with an electric beater.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Let set 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: butter sticks
directions: Melt margarine in an oblong pan.
Combine flour, sugar and milk; stir with fork until mixture clings together as for biscuit dough.
Place on floured board; knead until dough holds together. Roll into oblong shape.
Cut down center with knife; cut into 1 1/2-inch strips.
Place in pan of melted margarine.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for about 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: coconut kisses(need a kiss?  try these.)
directions: In a bowl, beat the egg whites and salt for three minutes. Add sugar and beat rapidly for 10 minutes.
Fold in vanilla and coconut.
Drop with a teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 250° oven for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dredge cranberries and nuts with 1 tablespoon flour.
Set aside.
In a measuring cup, combine eggs, shortening, orange juice, and orange rind.	Add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.	Sift dry ingredients together, twice.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients until well mixed.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool on a rack.
Wrap in foil and store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour in baked pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 275°.

title: chain gang candy
directions: Melt butter.
Add peanut butter, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately add oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir; pour into pan and chill or drop by tablespoon on waxed paper and chill.

title: moist coffee cake
directions: Put raisins in hot water and let stand to soften.
Combine all ingredients except[t fruit in a bowl and mix until eggs are completely blended.
Drain raisins, then add raisins and cherries to mix.
Pour into greased oblong or round pan.

title: honey corn bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat just until blended.
Pour into lightly greased pan or muffin cups.
Cook at 400° until golden brown.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Melt butter and shortening.
Add sugars.
Mix well.
Add egg. Beat until light colored.
Sift together flour and baking soda. Stir in shortening mixture.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Shape in rolls 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll in waxed paper.
Chill thoroughly.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in moderate oven at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: shrimp kabobs
directions: You will also need small wooden skewers.

title: tea time tassies
directions: Grease a miniature muffin pan and preheat oven to 350°. Cream together
butter
and
cream
cheese until well blended. Add flour and blend thoroughly.
Form 1-inch balls and flatten into muffin tins,
forming
a
crust
for
filling.
Add brown sugar and pecans to
egg;
mix well and fill each crust with 1 tablespoon of filling.
Bake
25 minutes; remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix until smooth and spread on cooled cake.

title: pork roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Wipe roast with damp paper towel.
Using a paring knife, make small deep slits in sides and top of roast. Insert garlic pieces into each slit.
Rub roast with salt and pepper.
Roast, uncovered, 25 minutes per pound.

title: hong kong pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a skillet, brown chops in oil and place in a rectangular casserole. Cover with onion slices, water chestnuts and mushrooms. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops. Cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes or until chops are tender. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Heat until melted.
When it comes to a good boil, add peanuts.
Cook until golden brown.
Then add salt and soda.
Mix well.
Pour into two greased cookie pans.
Takes about 25 to 30 minutes for this to cook.

title: coca-cola cake or squares
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Melt cocoa, margarine and Coke together and add to flour and sugar.
Add marshmallows, buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla and beat well, using mixer. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add next 8 ingredients, mixing well after each. Place in buttered 13 x 9 pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Blend into the creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini, chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon (heaping) onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until light brown.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: lime jello torte
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add rest of the ingredients. First cold water, then the rest.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: quick strawberry shortcake
directions: You will need a 9 x 13 x 2 cake pan.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Fill a well-oiled baking dish with ingredients; press bread cubes to moisten with tomatoes. Dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: miracle cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish to cover bottom and sides. Make a thin batter of flour, sugar and milk.
Mix and pour into buttered dish.
Over batter spread peaches.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
The batter will rise through the fruit and form a crust.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix the nuts and coconut.
Spread in bottom of greased 10 or 14-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix cream cheese, oleo and vanilla.
Gradually stir in 1 pound powdered sugar.
Spoon this over cake mix and spread out as much as possible.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot corned beef sandwich
directions: Mix altogether and spread on buns.
Wrap in foil and bake in oven about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: salsa
directions: In pan, saute oil, chopped onion and garlic until tender.
Add tomatoes and all spices.
Cook until all flavors are blended. Freezes well.

title: mushroom chicken wings
directions: Coat wings with flour. Saute 1/2 of onion in deep fat until clear. Add wings and fry until brown. Place fried wings in baking pan. Cover with 1/2 onion, bell pepper and celery. Pour on can of mushroom soup and 1/2 can of water. Bake at 350° until done (20 to 30 minutes).

title: banana boats
directions: With knife, starting at stem end, cut through top peel of banana (along inside curve) from one end to the other.
Spread banana apart and fill with chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Wrap each banana tightly in plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, pumpkin pie spice, and pecans.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars until light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients; mix just until moistened.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4 loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until tooth pick comes out clean.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses.
Mix until well blended.
Add balance of ingredients and mix well. Chill about 2 hours.
Roll in nuts and chill.
Makes 2 cheese balls.

title: freezer salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil one minute; let cool.
Combine broccoli, cauliflower and the rest of ingredients in a bowl.
Add cooled vinegar mixture and toss.
Cover.
May be frozen up to 1 month.
To serve, thaw in refrigerator for 8 hours.
May be frozen in smaller portions for individual servings.

title: margie wright's chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil, melted chocolate and sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in salt, flour and baking powder.
Chill dough overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop teaspoonful of dough balls into confectioners sugar.
Roll around until coated.
Place about 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies will crack while baking. Add 1/2 cup pecans, if desired.
Yield:
50 cookies.

title: chicken livers(stuffed)
directions: Wash and dry chicken livers; cut livers in half.
Marinate about 1 hour in soy sauce, oil, sugar, garlic and curry powder mixed real good.
Then wrap sliced water chestnut with chicken liver and then bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Ready to serve.

title: overnight bundt coffee cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Place frozen dough rolls into pan.
Pour melted butter over dough.
Sprinkle with mixture of pudding mix, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Leave out on counter overnight to rise.
Bake first thing in the morning in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Invert on platter and serve immediately.

title: diabetic chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and side of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Wrap outside of pan with aluminum foil.
In the bowl of a food processor or blender, puree all ingredients until smooth.
Do in 2 batches if necessary.
With a rubber spatula, scrape mixture into prepared pan.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 45 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Leave in oven with door closed for 1 hour.
Remove and refrigerate.

title: amy's pie
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday salad
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients, while heating, until dissolved and well blended.
Using large can of evaporated milk, which has been chilled, whip until stiff.
Fold in cooled mixture and put in refrigerator to chill.

title: osso buco
directions: Mix flour and white pepper.
Pat veal dry and dredge in flour mixture.
Brown all sides in oil/butter in Dutch oven.
Arrange meat on sides so marrow does not fall out.
Add herbs (except parsley), onion, 2 cloves garlic, carrots, and celery.
Cover and cook on high 10 minutes, stirring or shaking occasionally.
Add liquids and cook approximately 2 hours or until tender.
Mix last clove of garlic, parsley and lemon rind.
Sprinkle over shanks as garnish.
Serve with buttered egg noodles or plain boiled potatoes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice; pour over crust. Add layers of other remaining ingredients, sprinkling chopped pecans on top. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: best ever chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add mayonnaise, cold water and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Line two (9-inch) cake pans with waxed paper and divide batter evenly between pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Works well in 8-inch pans.

title: cream cheese chicken ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Mix together both cream cheeses, chicken, Worcestershire sauce and spices.
Form into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Put half in bowl.
Add onions, tomatoes and cucumber.
Add another layer of spaghetti and repeat, then add Italian dressing and mix well.
Sprinkle on salad the seasoning from package.

title: magic bars(makes 24 to 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs (will cover completely).
Top with remaining ingredients; press down. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice all apples.
Set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients together in a large bowl. Add apples and mix well. Make sure all apples are coated.
Butter and flour pie dish.
Put in bottom crust.
Put in apples and put on top crust.
Flute edges.
Poke fork holes all around pie.
Mix 1 egg yolk with a little milk and brush all over pie.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onion until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 4 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, rinse well, drain and squeeze out water.
Mix together sour cream, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add dressing mix and bacon bits.
Add spinach, mixing again.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix very well.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and ice cake.

title: mexican vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add taco seasoning, tomato juice, tomato paste, chili beans and frozen vegetables.
Mix well. Bring to a boil; simmer one hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve with chips and cheese.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix on low speed with mixer about 5 minutes.
Will keep in refrigerator a long time.

title: mom's easy sausage roll-ups
directions: Wrap a biscuit around each sausage and pinch it to keep it in place.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
You can use 1/2 a biscuit if you want a smaller roll-up.

title: mom's 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Make a custard with egg yolks, lemon juice, cream or milk and butter or margarine.
Mix together and cook in double boiler until it thickens.
Cool.
Mix together the marshmallows, pineapple (well drained), cherries and chopped nuts.
Pour dressing over all and gently mix.
Whip cream and fold in.
Allow to set in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: sour cream cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle the cucumbers with salt.
Let stand 15 minutes. Drain liquid.
Add onions, vinegar and pepper.

title: company potato bake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 inch pan.
Place frozen hashbrowns in pan with cheese.
In separate bowl mix soup, sour cream, 1/2 c. margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Mix gently with potatoes and cheese.
Add topping of 1/2 c. melted margarine and crushed cornflakes mixed together.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: black bean and salsa salad
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Blend salsa with red wine dressing.
Pour over salad and toss well. Cover and chill.
Serves 8.
Nice cold salad for summer.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix cake mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut cake to fit bottom of a trifle dish.
Next pour on a layer of pudding (prepared by box instructions).
Then layer with Cool Whip.
Next layer of cake, followed by pudding and Cool Whip for a second time.
Then crush Oreos, M&M's or Heath bar on top.

title: pork chops in scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown meat in margarine in a large skillet.
Season to taste. Place half of the potatoes in 2-qt. shallow casserole.
Cover with cheese slices.
Add remaining potatoes.
Arrange chops over potatoes.
Pan fry onions in drippings in skillet.
Add soup. Blend milk into the soup mixture slowly. Heat and pour over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: brendan's beer battered onion rings
directions: Batter; Blend the eggs, beer and spices.
Add the flour, mixing well.
The batter should be thick and creamy (if not, just adjust by adding more beer or flour).

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, butter and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Make 6 quarts of popcorn.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix real good.
Put in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: french onion drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Combine flour, butter, dip, and milk.
Mix well and drop from tablespoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Immediately after removing biscuits from oven, brush tops with butter.

title: orange salad
directions: Add dry jello mix to cottage cheese and mix real good.
Drain and cut oranges into small pieces.
Add to cottage cheese mixture. Fold in Cool Whip and chill.
Salad will thicken after cooling.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Mix dry ingredients together. Mix liquid shortening, buttermilk and yeast, then add dry ingredients. Mix well. On lightly floured surface, roll 1/2 recipe to rectangle, about 1/4 inch thick. Sprinkle with brown sugar and chopped pecans. Roll lengthwise as for jelly roll. Cut in 1 inch slices. Place on greased cookie sheet. Let set about 20 to 30 minutes. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Frost with confectioners icing.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the marshmallow cream, sugar, butter and salt. Bring to a boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over moderate heat.
Remove from heat. Gradually add all morsels until melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Pour into aluminum foil lined 12-inch square pan.
Cool in refrigerator until firm, about 2 hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Fix cake mix as directed on box.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle coconut and pecans on bottom of pan.
Pour cake batter evenly over coconut and pecans.
Cream together powdered sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Drop by spoonfuls the cream cheese mixture over cake mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham and rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put another 1/2 cup grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese parfaits
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted margarine.
Spoon into midget paper cups; pat down.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs (one at a time); beat with Mixmaster until blended.
Spoon (approximately 1 good size tablespoon or a little more) mixture into each muffin cup.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Add Thank You brand cherries, blueberries, etc., on top.

title: veal medallions with chanterelle mushrooms and champagne
directions: Place a large skillet on the stove on high heat and add 3 tablespoons of the olive oil.
Place the Chanterelles into the skillet and saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add 2 more tablespoons of oil to the skillet and add the button mushrooms and shallots.
Saute until the mushrooms are browned, about 5 minutes.
Add the bay leaves, thyme and tomato. Stir the mushrooms well and season, if necessary.
Pour in 1/4 cup of the champagne, the reduced beef stock and stir well to combine the ingredients.

title: squash casserole
directions: Place squash and onion in a boiler; pour enough water to cover squash.
Boil until squash is tender.
Add margarine; mix until margarine is melted.
Add saltine crackers; mix well, then add eggs.
Last, add cheese; mix well.
Pour squash mixture into a baking dish; bake at 375° until golden on top.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix potato and sugar.
Roll that mixture out flat.
Then spread the peanut butter over it.
Then roll it up like a jelly roll and cut into rounded pieces.

title: four-decker mocha dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl cut butter into flour until crumbly; stir in 3/4 cup peanuts.
Press mixture over bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
In a small bowl beat cream cheese until fluffy; beat in sugar and 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Chill.
In a large mixer bowl combine puddings and milk; beat 2 minutes.
Spoon on top of cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Sprinkle with remaining peanuts and grated chocolate.

title: lemon marinade
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Use as a marinade with fish.
Makes 2 servings, about 2 tablespoons each.

title: chicken crunch casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup, milk and salt.
Heat to boiling. Spread 1 1/2 cups potato chips on bottom of greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Pour in chicken mixture; cover with remaining chips.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: In large bowl, mix beef, eggs, bread crumbs, water, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Shape into meat balls.
Put meat balls on broiler pan; brown slightly on both sides.
Remove and put into the chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice.
Simmer about 45 minutes. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: french potato pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in two pie shells at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly in bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Set pan aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit into quarters; roll each piece in sugar mixture and layer in pan.
Combine brown sugar and melted butter; pour over dough. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before inverting onto serving platter.
Yield:
1 (10-inch) coffee cake.

title: peach glazed pork chops
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup. Add hot water to syrup to equal 1-1/2 cups. Mix syrup mixture and butter in large bowl until butter is melted. Stir in stuffing mix and peaches, let stand 5 minutes. Spoon stuffing mixture into 13 x 9 inch baking dish, arrange chops over stuffing. Mix preserves and mustard, spoon over chops. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until chops are done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and beaten eggs. Mix until well blended.
Stir in apples, walnuts, nuts and crushed pineapple.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date scotch pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Stir slowly into hot milk.
Cook all until thick.
Add egg yolks to mixture.
Cook 1 minute and remove from stove.
Add butter, vanilla, dates and pecans.
Cool and fold egg whites into mixture.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Put in refrigerator for at least one hour.
Serve topped with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a small mixing bowl, put bananas.
Beat with mixer on No. 3 speed until mashed.
Measure out 1 cup.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Put shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla into a large mixing bowl.
Beat on No. 8 speed for 2 1/2 minutes, scraping bowl while beating.
Stop mixer.
Add buttermilk or sour milk.
Add sifted flour mixture alternately with mashed banana while beating at No. 1 speed.
Scrape bowl while beating and beat only enough to blend, about 3 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: broccoli frittata
directions: Saute broccoli, onion, mushrooms, green pepper, salt and pepper in oil in 10-inch ovenproof skillet until broccoli is crisp-tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Combine eggs, liquid nonfat dry milk, cheese and basil and blend thoroughly. Stir into mixture in skillet.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut into wedges and serve immediately.

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; add milk, salt, pepper and margarine.
Cook until thickens; add bacon and drippings.
Serve with cornbread.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, saving 1/4 cup of juice.
Mix flour and sugar with pineapple.
Crumble crackers; melt butter and add both to flour and sugar mixture.
Add 1 cup cheese and the 1/4 cup pineapple juice.
Mix well and put into ovensafe casserole dish. Top casserole with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: stephen's chicken
directions: Put the chicken into the top of a double boiler with the cream, paprika, salt and pepper to taste and pinch of cayenne. Put over simmering water and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with cream and add to chicken mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Serves 6.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender and drain.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Saute onions in bacon drippings until tender. Blend in flour with next 5 ingredients and 1 cup water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in bacon and potatoes. Cook for 5 minutes, tossing lightly. Add eggs, tossing to mix.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook mixed vegetables for half the amount of time recommended on package. Combine all ingredients in pot with the vegetables. Heat all ingredients through for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir, then put in pie shell. Cover with second pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground chuck, stuffing mix, eggs and onion together.
Form into small balls.
Put in oven until brown.
Mix rest of ingredients in crock-pot; add meatballs.
Cook low about 4 hours.

title: season best shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients; chill. Serve with vegetables or chips. Yields 2 cups.

title: sweet and sour pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers
carefully
with
a
cloth.
Pack into a wide-mouth jar.
Cover
completely
with dark vinegar.
Cover, date and set aside for 80 days.
Add more vinegar if any seems to evaporate.
Pour
off
vinegar.
Do
not
wash
cucumbers. Slice cucumbers into
1/2 to 3/4 inch slices.
Pour sugar over them. Stir and
let
stand
for
1 hour.
Put into sterilized jars and adjust
lids.
Submerge
jars in boiling water for 10 minutes. Remove and
cool.
As the pickle mixture stands, the residual vinegar on the pickles mixes with the sugar and forms a syrup. Makes 8 pints.

title: mom's barbecue chicken
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and boil for 20 minutes.
Bake chicken at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour sauce over and cook 30 more minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Beat egg, baking powder and soda in buttermilk; add meal and grease.
Pour into greased irons and bake about 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add eggs to sugar and beat.
Add oil and beat.
Add pumpkin and blend.
Add dry ingredients with water.
Pour into 3 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can add nuts also, if desired.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of muffin cups.
Cook sausage and onions until brown, crumbling sausage and draining mixture on paper towels.
Stir together baking mix and mustard, then add sausage mixture, milk and cheese.
Blend together; do not beat.
Spread batter evenly in muffin cups to about 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until brown.
Makes about 12 muffins.
Serve warm.

title: sole for four
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lay 4 pieces of foil, each 10 inches long, on counter shiny-side up.
Place one fillet in center of each.
Place 1 teaspoon butter, 1 tablespoon orange concentrate and chopped green onion on each.
Wrap and seal.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.
The extra juice makes a nice sauce. Serve with rice and mandarin orange salad.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Pour into 18 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes, until done.
Blend cream cheese, pudding and milk with beater.
Fold in pineapple.
Spread on cooled cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: chicken and cashews
directions: Cook chicken (boil in large pot).
Remove when done and pull off bone.
Reserve 2 tablespoons liquid.
Pull off skin and shred chicken.
Heat oils and soy sauce in a large skillet.
Add chicken; heat through and add scallions, broth and nuts.
Cook until hot.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Line muffin pan with paper baking cups. Place approximately 1/2-inch of mixture in each cup.
Freeze.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water, peanut butter morsels; stir until smooth.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine butter and sugar.
Beat well.
Blend in melted morsels.
Beat in eggs and vanilla extract alternately.
Blend in flour mixture and milk.

title: cheese bacon bites(pampered chef recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll crescent rolls, leaving 2 rectangles together.
Pinch seams.
(You will have 4 rectangles.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cream cheese
and
soup together.
Stir in chicken; add other ingredients
except
cheese
and
mix well.
Thin to right consistency with
broth.
Grease casserole dish and pour mixture into dish.
Add
grated
cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 375° oven or until bubbly all over top.

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Mix other ingredients, then add yeast water.
Mix well.
Cover and set in refrigerator for at least 3 or 4 hours.
Roll and cut like biscuits.
Bake at 450°.

title: rocky road cake
directions: Grease and flour a 12-cup fluted tube or Bundt pan.
In small bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat together cake mix, eggs, real mayonnaise and water just until blended.
Increase speed to medium; beat 2 minutes. Stir in nut mixture.
Pour in prepared pan.

title: indian pudding
directions: Scald milk in top of a double boiler, or over low heat. Slowly drizzle corn meal into milk, stirring constantly until thickened, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend sugar, baking soda and spices; stir into the liquid.
Add molasses and cold milk, mixing well.
Add raisins, if desired.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 275° oven for 2 hours.
Serve warm with cream.
Serves 6.

title: overnight salad
directions: Put beaten egg in double boiler; add vinegar and sugar.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Cool.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Put in pan.
Store in fridge for 24 hours.

title: potatoes whipped with cheese
directions: Lightly salt potatoes.
Blend in the next 8 ingredients, beating constantly.
The mixture should be fairly moist.
If not, add a bit of cream and more butter.
Pile into an ovenproof serving dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot spinach artichoke dip
directions: Boil artichokes and spinach in 1 cup of water for approximately 10 minutes. Drain and mix softened cream cheese and the rest of the ingredients.
Serve warm with small bread or tortilla chips.

title: orange pineapple ice cream
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water.
Let cool.
Beat eggs at medium speed in large bowl with electric mixer until frothy. Add sugar, mixing well.
Stir in gelatin and remaining ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer container and freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Yields about 1 gallon.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 7 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Mix together the cream cheese and 1 cup sugar; beat well.
Add the Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Dissolve the jello in the hot water.
Add the frozen sliced strawberries (separate berries with knife).
When berries have thawed and jello begins to thicken, pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: mocha pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a heavy medium saucepan, combine chocolate and 1/4 cup of coffee liqueur.
Melt over low heat, stirring until smooth.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, vanilla and salt.
Beat until blended.
Add melted chocolate mixture and blend well.
Stir in melted butter and pecans.
Pour filling into pie shell and bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until pie is barely set in the center.
Transfer to a rack to cool.
Before serving, whip the cream with remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons coffee liqueur until soft peaks form.
Serve a generous amount of whipped cream with each slice.

title: sunday brunch bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine eggs, Dari-Mate, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, broccoli, bacon bits, onion and cheese.
Pour into Pam sprayed 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.
If refrigerated (pre-made) bake at 375°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: apple pancakes
directions: In an 8-inch frypan, melt butter and brown sugar.
Slice large, tart apple and saute.
Mix Egg Beaters and white sugar and beat in Jiffy mix.

title: peanut pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni, peas and carrots according to directions. Drain and chill in cold water.
Place macaroni and vegetables in a bowl and toss with peanuts, cheese, chopped egg and onion.
In a small bowl combine mayonnaise, mustard, relish, salt and pepper. Stir into macaroni mixture.
Chill until serving time.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix soft cream cheese, taco sauce and green onions.
Pour into dish and chill for 1 hour.
Top with Cheddar cheese, chopped lettuce and chopped tomato.
Serve with taco chips.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, soda and cinnamon.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken pesto pizza
directions: Preboil or brown chicken pieces in skillet.
Spread pesto sauce evenly over pizza crust.
Sprinkle just enough cheese to cover.
Spread chicken, onions and peppers on top of cheese.
May sprinkle more cheese on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° just until crust is browned.

title: mom's zucchini bread
directions: Mix well by beating on high for 3 minutes.
Blend 1/2 cup of chopped nuts coated with flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and add remaining ingredients.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Combine beef, egg, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, salt, onion and pepper.
Form into balls.
Brown in fat; drain.
Cook oil and pineapple juice over low heat for a few minutes.
Add cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, water and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Add meat balls and pineapple.
Good cover rice when used as a main dish.

title: hungarian short ribs
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat in hot oil.
Add onions.
Blend together the tomato sauce, 1 cup of water, brown sugar, vinegar, salt, dry mustard and Worcestershire and pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Skim off fat.
Stir in noodles and second cup of water.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, for 15 to 20 minutes more or until noodles are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.
Delicious with homemade noodles.

title: pizza cups
directions: In a skillet cook sausage meat over medium heat; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce, ketchup and garlic powder; set aside.
Press biscuits into 20 well-greased muffin cups.
Spoon 1 or 2 tablespoons of the meat mixture into each biscuit.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken royal
directions: Combine chicken, stuffing mix, mayonnaise, chicken broth, onion and eggs in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter.
Put rice on top of butter.
Add soup, water and mushrooms.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients. This makes 1 gallon of concentrate.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Add buttermilk and egg, stirring until combined.
Melt butter in skillet or baking pan. Pour in batter.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: six in one cookies(makes 18 dozen)
directions: Dough:
Cream butter; gradually add sugars.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Put rhubarb and sugar in a stainless steel pan and let sit overnight.
In the morning, bring to a boil for several minutes, then add jello.
Stir.
When cool, refrigerate.

title: streusel topped sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sweet potatoes, syrup and peel until well blended; spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix flour, oats, sugar and cinnamon in medium bowl; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crescents beef appetizers
directions: Saute
ground
beef;
drain
well and stir in dry onion soup mix.
Stir in cheese after mixture has cooled.
Roll out crescent dough
and cut each in half, making a smaller triangle.
Place
a heaping teaspoon of meat mixture on each triangle.	Roll
to close,
tucking point under roll or press edge together
with
a fork.
Bake
in a 375° oven on an ungreased cookie	sheet.	Serve warm.
Will
freeze
well.	Reheat in a 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt the butter in a deep baking dish or 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In another dish, mix the sugar, flour, baking powder and sweet milk.
Pour mixture over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour the pie cherries (juice and all) over this.
Do not stir.
Pour over this 3/4 cup sugar. Do not stir. Bake in a 325° oven for
1 hour. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Delicious with other fruits also.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients together with electric mixer.
Pour into crust and freeze until solid (a minimum of 4 hours).
Pie cuts best if it is at room temperature about 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 2 pies.
If you prefer 1 very tall pie, use the following:
8 ounce cream cheese, 1 cup peanut butter, 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar, and 12 ounces Cool Whip.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: chicken and pasta salad
directions: Prepare salad dressing mix with wine vinegar, water and salad oil as directed on the package, set aside.

title: flan
directions: Melt 1 cup sugar in saucepan.
Mix all ingredients except cinnamon together and pour into casserole or pie plate or if you don't have one, use a 7x
12-inch Pyrex casserole.
Mix milk and a can of water and blend in the eggs and 5 tablespoons of the sugar. Sprinkle with the cinnamon and bake in water bath about 1-inch of water in large pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve in the pan or unmold after it is cooled.

title: cream cheese bridge sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese with enough mayonnaise to soften.
Combine all ingredients and spread on small squares of pumpernickel bread or bridge cut outs.
Garnish with gherkins, olives and pimento. Makes 12 servings.

title: savoy cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage as you would lettuce and cook in small amount of salted water.
Drain.
Cook rice in double the amount of water, seasoned with chicken seasoning.
Combine all ingredients except Parmesan and bread crumbs.
Spread 1/2 mix into 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 mix crumbs and Parmesan.
Repeat.
Bake just before serving at 350° until top browns and casserole is heated through.

title: diane's cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and stir.
Add eggs, salt and butter.
Add sifted flour (it is sticky).
Turn over on board; add more flour until not so sticky.
Put in large crock or container and let rise for 5 hours.
Divide into 3 parts and just enough flour to permit rolling.
Brush with melted butter-sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Cut 1 1/4 inch thick; put in well greased pan.
Don't cover.
Let sit for 8 hours or overnight.
Bake 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost.
May be frozen.
Makes 50-55 rolls.

title: clark bars
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix with cornflakes.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: apple-potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets in boiling salted water until tender.
Cook and peel.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight. Quarter, core and chop apples in a medium size bowl.
Toss with lemon juice to prevent discoloring.
Combine apples, onion, celery and dill pickle in a large salad bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper in a small bowl; mix well.
Pour into salad bowl; toss ingredients until blended. Slice potatoes into salad a few at a time, tossing after each addition.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Taste and add additional dressing, if needed.
Garnish the salad with hard-cooked egg wedges.
Serves about 8.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix ingredients on high speed mixer until completely blended. Chill before serving.

title: mama's buttermilk biscuits
directions: In a bowl combine the flour, baking powder, soda and salt; cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in buttermilk.
Knead dough gently.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with a biscuit cutter and place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake and bake in 2 (9-inch) pans.
Cool.
Pull thread through each layer (4 pieces).
Mix remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Put lots of mixture between layers and the remainder on top and sides.
Refrigerate for 2 or 3 days before serving (if you can wait).

title: player's easy chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix well dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Chop onions, tomatoes and lettuce.
Toss these with choice of dressing.
Crunch Doritos and add to salad.
Slice avocado; add to salad.
Chill.

title: louisiana rice griddle cakes
directions: Use leftover or freshly cooked rice. Place in saucepan with about a half cup of water and overcook (very soft). Separate eggs. Beat egg yolks; add milk, oil, salt, sugar, flour and soft rice, stirring after each addition. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake on hot griddle until bubbles burst in center. Turn only once. Note: Batter may be made the previous day, but omit baking powder and egg whites. Add these at the last minute.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar and Crisco oil.
Add eggs and beat.
Dissolve baking soda in water.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture alternately with water.
Add pumpkin and mix.
Spray pans.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Snap heads of largest mushrooms.
Dice stems and remaining mushrooms and saute ingredients with bread crumbs.
Stuff large mushrooms with mixture and brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: super bean dip
directions: In microwavable bowl, cook beans and liquid for 5 minutes. In medium saucepan, add beans with liquid, cream cheese, taco mix, sour cream and onions.
Heat thoroughly.
With masher, mash ingredients.
Serve with chips.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Let stand overnight before serving.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Cream together the softened cream cheese with the sugar until fluffy.
Mix Dream Whip by directions on box (both envelopes). Fold in cream cheese. Fill crusts with mixture.
Top with blueberries. Chill overnight.
May use other pie fillings for toppings.
Makes 2 pies.

title: poppy seed cookies
directions: Combine oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time and beat well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oatmeal, poppy seed and orange juice.
Refrigerate one hour or more.
Roll out on floured board and cut with cookie cutter.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° on lightly greased cookie sheet for ten to twelve minutes.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over cut chicken wings.
Marinate overnight, mixing them up every once in a while.

title: nachos
directions: Arrange tortilla chips on a cookie sheet.
Spoon salsa on chips.
Sprinkle chips with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let cool 1 minute before eating. Or you may cook in the microwave in a safe dish.
Set 100% High power; cook for 30 to 40 seconds.

title: caramel pudding
directions: Remove label from can.
Place can in pan of water to fill until can is covered.
Boil for 4 hours.
Cool.
Open can.
Add whipped cream as a topping.

title: feta cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Mix walnuts, zwieback and butter.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: mom's venison jerky
directions: Cut meat into strips approximately 1/2 x 1-inch and any length.
Trim all fat off.
Hammer with meat hammer, turn over strips and hammer again.
If you don't have a meat hammer, jag the meat with a fork.

title: tree bark
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
In saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth, melt the chips together.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanuts spread out on cookie sheet. Refrigerate about 1 hour. Break into pieces. Store in container that seals tight.

title: marriage cake
directions: Combine love, trust, understanding and kindness until thoroughly blended.
Sift together friendship and common sense. Add to love mixture.
Moisten well with tears of joy and sorrow. Pour into large heart shaped pan, well oiled with the Holy Spirit. Sprinkle with the spice of variety.
Bake in a moderate oven warmed by God's presence.
Garnish with children, as desired.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and vanilla; beat in egg.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg or spice you like.
Peel and grate or chop raw apples.
Add flour mixture and apples to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes in greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Serve warm or cooled.
Good with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients of basic meatball mixture with garlic and 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning, mixing lightly but thoroughly. Shape beef mixture into 12 meatballs.
Brown meatballs in hot oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Pour off drippings.
Add stewed tomatoes, tomato paste, water, remaining 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning and sugar to meatballs in skillet, stirring to combine. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.

title: hot wings
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper, garlic powder and allspice.
Roll chicken wings, cut in half, in flour mixture; fry in oil about 350° until cooked through.
Mix butter, Tabasco sauce and hot sauce in saucepan until butter is melted and hot.
Dip chicken pieces into sauce; place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes. Serve with favorite vegetables.
(Omit Tabasco sauce for warm wings.)

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onion.
Add all other ingredients. Finally add the 3 cans of beans.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, parsley and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Sprinkle broccoli with 1/2 teaspoon salt and the garlic salt.
Layer half each of the noodles, cottage cheese mixture, broccoli, cheese slices and Parmesan cheese in an ungreased 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Repeat. Arrange bacon slices on lasagne.
Bake, uncovered, about 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: a great salad(servings:  4)
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O; add ginger ale.
Let set up slightly and add the other ingredients.
Let set up in refrigerator and ice with topping.

title: grandmother's cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add pineapple and beaten eggs. Mix together.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and raisins.
Sprinkle this over raw cake and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour three 1 pound coffee cans.
Fill 1/2 full. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Can use 2 loaf pans.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot. If desired, tie whole spices in cheesecloth. (If spices are added loose, strain before serving.) Cover and set on low for 2 to 8 hours. Serve from crock-pot with ladle.

title: baked beans(hearty enough for a meal)
directions: Brown and drain beef, onion and bacon.
Put meat mixture in large casserole dish along with all cans of beans (undrained). Add sugar, brown sugar, dry mustard and molasses.
Mix thoroughly. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wagon wheel cheese dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese and mayonnaise; season with paprika. Put olives, relish, onion, garlic clove and green pepper through a food chopper.
Add cheese and remaining ingredients together; blend thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator.
Better made a day or 2 earlier.

title: mary's artichoke dip
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: clam and corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, saute celery and onion in butter.
Stir in water, macaroni, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes, or until macaroni is tender.
Stir in milk, corn and clams; cook just until heated through.
Yields 6 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: smoked sausage stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry meat until brown; put in bowl.
Put all vegetables in pan; stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Return meat.
Mix bouillon, cornstarch and soy sauce; pour over all.
Stir-fry until sauce is slightly thickened.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Use roasting pan for popped corn.
Keep popped corn warm in 250° oven.
Mix all ingredients, except soda in large saucepan. Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add soda.
(Be careful, foams when stirring.)
Stir well and pour over popped corn.
Coat well with large spoon. Return to oven and bake 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Place in pie shell.
Sprinkle grated cheese, flour and onion on top.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over mixture in pie shell.
Sprinkle parsley on top; bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine.
Add cocoa.
Stir until smooth. Stir in sweetened condensed milk, water and eggs.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Put sugars, vanilla and cream cheese in blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
Serve with a colorful assortment of seasonal fruit.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set in refrigerator overnight for better flavor.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
May be eaten with crackers.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter, oil and sugar; add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add to creamed mixture. Pour 3/4 of batter in 13 x 9-inch pan, which has been sprayed with Pam.
Spread pie filling on top; sprinkle with nuts.
Pour remaining batter on top.
(It won't cover completely.)
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: simple and great coconut cake
directions: Make 3 or 4-layer cake by package directions.
Let cool completely.
Cream together the sour cream and sugar; mix in coconut.
By hand, fold in Cool Whip.
Frost the cake.

title: sauteed carrots and zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into
2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Cut carrots into matchstick strips.
Cut green onions into 2-inch pieces.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cold water.
Add the thawed strawberries and the undrained pineapple, then add the banana slices.
Pour half of this into a 9 x 13-inch dish; refrigerate until set well enough to spread the sour cream on top. Add the remaining half of the Jell-O mixture carefully, so that it remains on top.
Continue to refrigerate until well set.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add sherbet just before serving.
Yields 30 servings.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into two graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate approximately 2 hours before serving.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Heat mustard and jelly until dissolved. Add wieners.
Keep warm.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add frozen broccoli and cook until broccoli starts to separate (don't cook too much).
Add all other ingredients and bake together in baking dish at 350° (covered) for about 20 minutes.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Mix well with a pastry blender.
Cut in oleo until mixture is crumbly.
Set aside 1 cup of the mixture. Add egg, milk, soda, salt and vanilla to remaining mixture.
Beat well.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Leaving wrapper on candy, crush with hammer.
Add nuts and reserved crumb mixture. Spread over batter.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt in saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup milk; stir constantly.
Cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Cook until lukewarm.
Beat in 3/4 box confectioners sugar.
Put on cake and enjoy.

title: green bean sandwich roll-up
directions: Marinate overnight in Italian dressing. Mix cream cheese and Italian seasoning together.
Spread on white sandwich size bread. Cut edges off.
Place 3 beans in a line on bread and roll over beans. Cut 3/4 inch rounds. Yields 25 to 30 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix, boil, cool and add all ingredients to cucumbers.
Keep well in refrigerator.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together,
cutting
shortening into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and
stir
to	soft dough.
Don't knead dough, just roll it out on floured board and cut.
Brush top with buttermilk and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: bunny rabbit salad
directions: Wash lettuce; dry.
Place leaf on each plate.
Place pear half upside down on each plate.
At small end, add raisins or cloves for eyes and 2 almond halves for ears.
Add 1 teaspoon of cottage cheese at base of large end for a tail.
Eat!

title: aunt bert's coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate eggs.
Add melted butter to yolks and sugar.
Beat lightly.
Add flour, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Pour blueberry pie filling in 9 x 13-inch dish. Pour crushed pineapple over top of blueberries. Sprinkle sugar/cinnamon mixture next. Pour dry cake mix on top, breaking up any lumps. Melt butter and pour on top. Bake at 375° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes. Top should be bubbly and turning brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour. Add seasonings, celery and broth. Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Add half of the sauce to the spaghetti. Place in a greased, shallow casserole. Add chicken and mushrooms to the remaining sauce.
Pour over the spaghetti. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: homemade macaroni & cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350° Make white sauce with margarine, flour, milk & salt (on stove top). Bring to a boil, and let it get thick (only boil for 1/2 min.). Add 1 1/2 cups cheese to sauce. Boil macaroni until tender and drain. Stir all together with macaroni. Put into baking dish and add cheese to top. Bake 20 - 25 min.

title: beef 'n noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In a large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter 3 minutes or until tender.
Add beef and cook until no longer pink.
Drain excess fat.
In a medium bowl, combine tomato paste and sour cream; stir in noodles and cottage cheese.
Layer half the noodle mixture in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with half the beef mixture; repeat.
Pour tomato sauce evenly over the top of the casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: crepes(breakfast pancakes)
directions: In a medium bowl, beat the softened cream cheese with an electric
mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Add whipping cream and vanilla.
Beat mixture on low speed until combined.
Stir in the powdered sugar.
To serve, spoon 2 Tbsp. of filling onto each thin pancake and roll up.
Sprinkle with additional powdered sugar and top with fresh berries.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crunchy fruit and cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and lemon juice in blender and blend until smooth. Stir in other ingredients and blend. Cover and chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Cream oleo, confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Mix milk, pudding mix and whipped topping dessert. Combine.
Layer mixture and crushed Oreos (dirt).
Make sure the last layer is the crumbled Oreo to look like dirt.
Use the gummi worms as you layer mixtures.
Put this in the flower pot with fake flowers in the center.
Use trowel for serving.
Presto.
Dirt cake.

title: date and nut balls
directions: Mix
and
cook	for
minutes in heavy pan. Take off stove and add 1 cup nuts and 2 cups Rice Krispies.
When cool enough
to handle,
butter hands and shape in balls.	Roll in coconut or nuts.

title: oyster stew
directions: Cover oysters with water.
Simmer until edges curl.
Skim. Pour into milk.
Add butter.
Season to taste.
Serve with a dash of paprika.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hungarian pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of oil.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Add spices to taste.
Heat gently.
Add mushrooms. Cover pork chops with sauce and bake in slow oven at 300° until pork is tender.

title: jungle stew
directions: *Hold until last.
Save the bacon grease.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add soup and milk; stir.
Put 1/2 broccoli in greased casserole.
Layer 1 cup crackers and 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Dot with butter.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas barbecue
directions: Brown meat well in drippings.
Then add onions and sauce. Simmer slowly most of the day, 5 to 6 hours, until very tender. Remove any bones.
Slice meat and return to sauce.

title: cottage cheese "hamburgers"
directions: Combine cottage cheese, eggs, 3/4 cup bread crumbs, onion and green pepper.
Form into patties; coat with bread crumbs and brown in butter.
Serve plain or with chili sauce or catsup.

title: chicken dinner in foil
directions: Heat oven to 370°.
Cut 4 twelve inch squares of heavy duty foil.
Place 3 Tbsp. raw rice in center of foil.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and put 2 pieces on rice.
Divide mushrooms into 4 parts and add, portion out zucchini, green pepper and onion and put on top.
Turn up sides of foil.
Mix tomato sauce, mushroom liquid, oregano and basil, pour sauce on chicken.
Fold foil over food and seal, leave room on top for steam.
Put in shallow baking pan and bake in preheated oven 1 hour.
Open packets and sprinkle cheese on top, and serve.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick, stirring constantly, over low heat.
Cool thoroughly.

title: texas brownies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar.
In heavy saucepan, combine margarine, shortening, coffee or water and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well, using wooden spoon or high speed of mixer.
Pour into a well-butter 17 1/2 x 11-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brownies test done in center.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion in hot fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water and

title: peach refresher
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cream margarine with cream cheese. Mix in flour, a small amount at a time, creaming after each addition. Chill dough for about 2 hours. Break off walnut sized pieces of dough and pat into lightly greased 1-inch muffin cups, covering sides and bottom of cups.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening; beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift flour together and add sugar mixture alternating with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in 3 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar, eggs and pumpkin pie filling.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and pumpkin pie spice.
Mix all together.
Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan.
Pour ingredients into pan and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Then bake at 300° until cake is done.
Cool 45 minutes.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: You also need 24 cupcake liners.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Pour pie filling into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit. Dribble melted butter or margarine over all the dry cake mix. Top with nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serve hot or cold topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: tecky's tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles, drain and return to pan.
Stir in tuna, sour cream, milk, onion, 1/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with croutons.
Put about 5 or 6 dabs of butter around the top of the croutons.
Completely cover croutons with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops fricasseed
directions: Spread both sides of pork chops with mustard.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Dip well in flour.
Brown on both sides in just enough fat to brown nicely.
Add chicken noodle soup.
Cover and simmer until very tender.

title: margaret's stir-fry vegetables
directions: In large nonstick skillet, heat half of oil over medium heat. Add onion, garlic, mushrooms and sweet pepper and stir-fry until tender, about 4 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove to side dish and set aside.
Heat remaining oil in skillet, add eggplant, zucchini and stir-fry 4 minutes, until tender.
Return mushroom mixture to pan.
Add tomatoes, thyme and basil.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: supper salad
directions: Put ingredients in a bowl; mix lightly.
Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles; drain.
Cook hamburger and drain.
Add Manwich and simmer a few minutes.
Layer ingredients: noodles, hamburger and cheese in large pan until pan is almost full.
Bake until bubbly and brown on top in 400° oven.

title: meat and cheese dip
directions: Cook one pound of hamburger meat. Cook
1/2 pound sausage. Drain and combine.
Add 1 box of Velveeta cheese. Stir well. Cook on slow or put in crock pot on lowest temperature. Add one can of tomatoes with green chilies and peppers. Cook on low heat. Buy chips and eat up!

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour seasoned with salt and mustard.
Cut bacon 1 inch pieces; fry in Dutch oven.
Remove bacon pieces; add beef to bacon drippings.
Brown beef on all sides.
Add soup mix and Veg-All liquid plus water to give you 3 cups.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add tomato juice, sugar and barley.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add bacon and Veg-All home-style vegetables.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bully pudding
directions: Mix the flour with nuts and dates.
Cream the sugar, butter and eggs together.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour (check in 45 minutes).
Serves 8.
Whipped cream may top it.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine first three ingredients; beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to the egg mixture along with the vanilla.
Fold in apple, walnuts and coconut.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Tear up bread, put on bottom of pan.
Brown and drain sausage and put over bread.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over sausage.
Beat eggs and milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over top.
Can be stored overnight in fridge.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: salt pork and gravy
directions: After frying several pieces of country ham in a heavy skillet, remove ham and pour off fat.
Return pan to heat.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup water or strong coffee and stir. Cook long enough to dissolve all extract from pan.

title: potato candy
directions: Take cold potato and mash. Mix with powder sugar until stiff. Then roll it out. Spread with peanut butter. Sprinkle with a little powder sugar. Roll up and put in refrigerator to chill.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients
and
spices
in	bowl. Toss with apples.
Preheat
oven to 425°.
Spoon apples and mixture into your
favorite
pie
crust.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and dot with margarine.
Place crust lid on top with a little milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in oven about 425° until it is done (light brown).

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Have cream cheese and sour cream at room temperature.
Beat together with mixer to blend well.
Add chopped olives, green onions and jalapeno slices.
Spread mixture on tortilla and roll up like a jellyroll.
Place seam side down.
Cut the ends off, then cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Insert toothpick in each pinwheel. Serve with a small bowl of picante sauce to dip in.

title: easy penuche icing
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan; add brown sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes stirring constantly.
