Stir in milk; bring to boil, stirring.
Cool to lukewarm; gradually add sugar.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and spices or extract.
Add squash, egg (slightly beaten) and milk gradually. Bake in pie shell in 425° oven for 10 minutes. Decrease temperature to 350° for 30 minutes until set.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour into large bowl. Place in freezer. Take out a little while before meal to let thaw.

title: fluffy 7-minute icing
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in top of double boiler, then place over boiling water (upper pan should not touch surface of water). Beat with electric beater 4 or 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and change the hot water for cold.
Replace the icing; add vanilla and syrup.
Beat until icing makes stiff peaks and holds shape. Spread on cake.
This recipe makes enough icing to cover the top and sides of two 8-inch or 9-inch layer cakes.

title: cheddar patties
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder onto waxed paper.
Add eggs, milk, oil, sugar and flavorings to mixing bowl.
Mix in dry ingredients and poppy seed well.
Pour into 3 greased aluminum loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Brush glaze on top.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, mix eggs, Karo syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: piquant sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients together; pour over meat loaf before cooking.
(This is very good over meat loaf.)

title: ancient chinese secret
directions: Salt and
pepper
chicken
and
bake
for 30 minutes at 350°. In oil, cook onion and bell pepper.
Cover chicken with onion and bell pepper.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and flour. Cover and simmer for 1 hour on low heat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Drain mushrooms and add juice to chicken broth to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into flour mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups of cream.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add rice, mushrooms, chicken and pimentos.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with almonds.

title: cream cheese and olive salad
directions: Crush soft cream cheese with a fork. Stir in cream, salt, paprika, olives and pimento.
Pack the cheese into a small straight glass.
Chill it until it is firm.
Cut it into slices. Serve it on watercress or lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: almond tea
directions: Measure
water into large saucepan.
Add sugar and let dissolve.
Bring mixture to a boil, then remove from flame.
Put tea bags in water for 3 or 4 minutes depending on strength desired.
Add extracts and lemon.
Stir and serve hot.
Can serve as iced tea drink.
Make stronger tea for serving over ice.
Makes 1 quart.

title: sugar-free frosty lemon pie
directions: Mix Equal into yogurt and set aside. Stir boiling water into gelatin powder until dissolved. Add ice cubes. Stir until melted, then stir in lemon concentrate. Finally, using a wire whip, whisk yogurt into gelatin mixture until smooth. Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate 2 1/2 to 3 hours (or place in freezer for no more than 30 minutes and then into refrigerator until ready). Garnish each pie slice with a mint sprig or orange slice.

title: white chili
directions: Cook and dice chicken.
Heat oil, add onion and cook until transparent.
Add garlic, chilies, cumin, oregano and chili powder. Add beans and broth.
Bring to boil.
Add chicken and salt to taste.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle each bowl of chili with Monterey Jack cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Stir in flour and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dill dip
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve as a dip for fresh vegetables.

title: pineapple coconut chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Refrigerate pies.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all dressing ingredients in blender.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cranberries, marshmallows and sugar. Refrigerate overnight. Add apples, grapes and pecans to cranberry mixture.
Mix well. Fold in whipped cream. Serve immediately.

title: baked hominy grits
directions: Combine grits and water.
Stir and boil for 3 minutes.
Add oleo, cheese, salt and egg mixture.
Bake in a greased casserole dish for 1 hour.

title: fruit topping
directions: In a small saucepan heat and stir apple jelly with the water until melted.
Cool slightly. Drain fruit, dry thoroughly.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together, add to first mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10-12 minutes. Makes 74 large cookies.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: golden egg sandwiches
directions: Chop eggs, onion, Spam and cheese.
Add all other ingredients. Pour on buns.
Broil until golden brown.
Garnish with slice of stiff butter.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake, eggs, oil, 1/2 cup rum, 1/2 can creme de coconut and 1/2 crushed pineapple.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (approximately).
Remove from oven.
Prick holes in warm cake and pour remaining creme de coconut mix plus 2 tablespoons rum over warm cake.
Top with crushed pineapple.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.
Better second day.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: In a large saucepan, combine apple cider or juice and brown sugar.
For spice bag, place cinnamon, allspice and the 1 teaspoon whole cloves in a double thickness cheesecloth.
Bring up corners of cheesecloth and tie with string.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer at least 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add peanut butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Make into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 15 minutes.

title: stove top baked potatoes
directions: Wash either baking or all-purpose potatoes, leaving skins on. Cut in half longways.
Heat a covered, heavy skillet.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
May add more margarine depending on how many potatoes you are making.
Turn heat to low. Add potatoes, cut side down.
I sprinkle seasoning blend (Nature's Seasons) on cut side of potato.
Cover.
Make sure heat is on low.
Cook for 30 minutes or longer.

title: icebox pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, raisins, graham cracker crumbs and vanilla together well. Cook on medium heat, stirring often. When the mixture is thickened, spread it 1/2-inch thick in a pan. Place in the refrigerator for several hours or overnight. Cut into small squares. Top squares with Cool Whip and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: salsa blanca(white sauce)
directions: Melt butter and mix cornstarch and flour.
Add milk little by little, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add lemon, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Put in a double boiler to keep warm if you are not going to use immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the chicken, cream of mushroom and sour cream together. Crumble the Ritz crackers on top, then add the melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add salsa.
Stir in cheese and chives or olives.
Spread thin layer on tortilla.
Roll tortilla tightly and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into bite size.
Serve with jar of salsa.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix all together and cook in saucepan on medium heat until thickened.
Pour over layers of vanilla wafers and sliced bananas. Top with meringue.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chips.
Serve with taco chips.

title: hot chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into large bowl and set aside.
Bring butter, cocoa, Crisco oil and water to a boil.
Add to flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, baking soda and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 14-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake in 375° preheated oven for 35 minutes.

title: spanish pork chops with rice
directions: Brown chops and onion in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, about 1 hour.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Mix cornstarch with a little of milk.
Bring rest of milk to boil and add the cornstarch and milk mixture; cook until bubbly and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add grated cheese, margarine, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Pour over buttered toast. Brown under broiler, if desired.
Serves 1 or 2.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Cook together oil, onion, tomatoes and jalapenos for 15 minutes, then add cumin, chili powder, Velveeta, cream cheese and sour cream.
Let simmer in crock-pot until blended. Serve with chips.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix squash, onions and bell peppers; salt to taste.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bring to boil sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Add squash, onions and peppers.
Boil 1 minute.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: white bean dip
directions: Soak bread crumbs in water.
In food processor or blender, combine and process remaining ingredients until almost smooth. Add bread crumbs; process until smooth. Chill for several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with toasted pita chips.

title: raised meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in refrigerator for several hours (overnight).
Form into balls and brown in small amount of shortening.
Place in pan with lid along with the soups mixed together and pour over meatballs.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.
Makes 75 small meatballs.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Add oleo, corn, 1 tablespoon onion and eggs.
Put in casserole.
Top with 1 tablespoon onion, dressing and bacon.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Put soda in buttermilk and dissolve.
Mix dry ingredients.
Make into balls.
Drop in flour and "pat" out.
Place on greased baking sheet; bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: savory lemon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
This is a wonderful dip for fresh vegetables, especially blanched fresh asparagus.

title: new york waldorf salad
directions: In a bowl mix apples, raisins, walnuts, chutney and mayonnaise.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon mixture into a serving bowl lined with lettuce leaves.
Chill until ready to serve. Serve with roast duckling or turkey.
Add slices of date-nut bread or Boston brown bread and a pitcher of sangria or fruit punch.

title: okra fritters
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients; stir in eggs, butter and milk.
Fold in okra; drop by teaspoons into hot grease.

title: shrimp and red pepper pasta
directions: Combine salad dressing and cheese. Set aside. Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain.

title: short cake(for strawberries)
directions: Beat eggs, shortening, sugar, salt, vanilla and baking powder together in large bowl.
Beat until sugar is dissolved.
Begin adding flour and beat it in; keep adding and beating in flour until you have a very soft dough.
Then take some of the mixture out on a floured board and knead a little.
Shape into rounds and bake at 350° to 375° until it's light brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until done; drain.
Chop onion, tomato, green pepper and cucumber.
Add chopped veggies to pasta; pour in salad dressing.
Add salad seasoning.
(You can add ham or chicken.)

title: java ice cream fizz
directions: Combine milk, sugar and instant coffee granules in a tall glass.
Add a spoonful of vanilla ice cream; stir until ice cream melts.
Add 2 scoops of vanilla ice cream; carefully pour in chilled ginger ale.
Makes 1 serving.

title: white chocolate mousse cake(12 servings)
directions: You also need food processor/blender, 2 medium bowls, 2 spoons, 9-inch spring-form pan, large microwavable bowl and a mixer.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut up chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Beat water, flour and egg together.
Dip chicken into batter.
Deep-fry until golden brown for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Salt to taste.

title: roast turkey
directions: Thaw turkey if frozen.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Remove giblets and discard.
Rinse turkey and pat dry.
Gently loosen skin from meat on breast and legs by breaking the membrane that holds the skin to the meat and sliding your hand between the two to loosen the skin.
Spread peppercorns under the skin and in the cavity. Stuff the cavity with apple and parsley.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust. Cover with other crust to make top.
Crimp edges to seal; slit top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: baked wild rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper until half done.
Add pimento and mushrooms; mix with rice.
Add chicken broth.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If dry, add additional broth. Serves 8.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients into dry mixture.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan, greased. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice quiche
directions: Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Add broccoli and onion; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until vegies are tender.
Drain well; set aside.
Combine rice, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 cup egg substitute and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Press evenly over bottoms and up sides of two 9-inch quiche dishes or pie plates, coated with spray Mazola.
Combine remaining 1 cup egg substitute, remaining salt, pepper, milk, mushrooms and broccoli mixture in a bowl; stir well.
Pour mixture into dishes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts (10 minutes).
Serves 12 (145 calories per serving).

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns enough to mix.
Add onions, 1/2 of cheese, celery, soup, sour cream and salt and pepper.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Add remaining cheese and corn flakes for topping.
Cook 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate bugels
directions: Pick out whole Bugles, stuff with peanut butter, and dip 1/2 of bugle into melted almond bark, holding small end.
Place onto wax paper to cool.

title: lemon crumb cake
directions: Bake cake mix either in 2 layers or in 13 x 9-inch pan. Crumble half of baked cake on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan and pack down tightly.
Blend sweetened condensed milk and lemonade and spoon over crumbs.
Crumble balance of cake and press over milk-lemonade mixture.
Spread on whipped topping and sprinkle coconut on top of whipped topping.
Make 2 to 3 days before serving and keep in refrigerator.
Simply delicious.

title: cream cheese cake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla together. Place in well-greased, oblong pan. Moisten hands with water or oil and press mixture evenly in pan. Beat 3 eggs, sugar, cream cheese and 1 teaspoon vanilla together. Pour over mixture in pan. Top with pecan pieces. Cook in preheated oven at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes. Check doneness; it may take a little longer. Top will still be soft when done. Let cool and cut. Keeps well when stored in a cool place.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Add cottage cheese, eggs and seasonings. Spoon into 8-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and dot with butter.
Bake in preheated oven at 325°
for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Place prepared pudding over cake.
Place drained pineapple over pudding.
Place pie filling over pineapple.
Cover pie filling with Cool Whip. Sprinkle nuts and coconut on top. Chill.

title: mom's chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, milk and cooked rice.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
In skillet, melt butter.
Pour in stuffing and stir until blended and toasted.
Spread over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until bubbling hot.
Do not cover while baking.
Makes 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice top off rolls; place ham and cheese on bottom.
Put top back on.
Add remaining ingredients to melted butter.
Pour on top of rolls.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Add flour until batter is stiff.
Sprinkle flour on waxed paper.
Roll out and cut cookies.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar well.
Add syrup, milk, vanilla, slightly beaten eggs and pecans.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust. Bake 45 minutes in moderate oven.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Heat soup with broth and slowly add cream, then sherry. Butter a large casserole or glass baking pan.
Add turkey, noodles and mushrooms. Pour liquid over top, then sprinkle with grated Parmesan or Cheddar cheese.
Top with toasted almonds.
Bake in hot oven until bubbly and browned on top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Drain corn and mix with soup in a bowl.
Add rice to the soup and rice mixture and stir well.
Pour in baking dish.
Slice butter on top.
Add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbling.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix well together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Glaze while still hot.

title: hot mexican spread
directions: In a pie plate, layer all ingredients in the order listed. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese and let melt. Dip with tortilla chips.

title: mom's easy baked sole
directions: Heat butter. Add garlic and tomatoes. Cook 30 seconds, stirring. Turn off heat and stir in cheese and basil.
Pour over fillets and add 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: turkey sausage pizza
directions: Spread sauce on cooked pizza crust, then put meat, diced peppers and onions over sauce.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese (grated).
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until cheese is golden.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Trim
all fat from steak.
Slice steak across the grain into thin
strips,
about
1/8-inch
wide
and 3 inches long. (Partially	frozen	meat
is
easier
to
slice.)
Heat oil in frypan.
Add
beef	strips;
stir-fry
over high heat, turning pieces
constantly,
until beef is no longer red, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Add carrots, celery, onion and seasonings. Cover
and cook until carrots are slightly tender, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add
squash;
cook
until
vegetables are tender-crisp, 3 to 4 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water until smooth. Add slowly
to beef mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened and vegetables are coated with a thin glaze.

title: cabbage with carrots and green onions
directions: Heat oil in nonstick frying pan.
Add onions, carrots, garlic and dry mustard.
Stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cabbage and vinegar.
Mix with vegetables in pan.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: old-fashioned chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until done.

title: spaghetti for twenty
directions: Brown meat and onions in margarine.
Add carrots, peppers, parsley and garlic.
Add tomatoes and soup, rinsing containers with a little water.
Simmer 1 hour. Add mushrooms and cook 20 more minutes.
Cook spaghetti in boiling, salted water until tender (about 20 minutes).
Rinse in cold water.
Have ready 3 large casseroles. In each put a layer of spaghetti, a layer of sauce, then grated cheese. Repeat with a second layer.
(May be set aside for baking later.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lentil casserole(an excellent vegetarian entree)
directions: Combine ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Stir well.
Add broth; stir.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Finely chop beef and onions.
Add to cream cheese mixture with remaining ingredients.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine cracker crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter or margarine.
Press evenly into a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: pretzel salad
directions: To make the crust, mix together crushed pretzels, margarine and the 3 tablespoons of sugar and pat into pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes; cool.

title: broccoli casserole(club member: laine)
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Heat mushroom soup and add cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add cooked broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish and top with croutons. Cook until golden brown at 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss first 3 ingredients.
Mix with dressing to coat.
Top with egg slices and croutons, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ingredients in order given.
Bake 30 minutes in 350°
oven.
Cut while warm.

title: hominy grits
directions: Pour hominy into salted boiling water; stir until it boils. Simmer heat for 45 to 60 minutes, stirring often.
When ready to serve, add 2 tablespoons butter.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta 6 to 8 minutes. Rinse thoroughly with cold water. Mix cucumber, tomatoes and onion. Add 1 tablespoon of the seasoning packet and a little Italian dressing. Add vermicelli, more dressing and 1 tablespoon of seasoning.
Mix thoroughly.
Add the rest of the Italian dressing and 1 last tablespoon of the seasoning mix. Stir all together and refrigerate.

title: spiced nuts(appetizer in microwave)
directions: Place margarine in 3-quart casserole dish.
Microwave at High for 45 to 60 seconds.
Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Add nuts, stirring to coat.
Microwave 7 to 12 minutes.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
Spread on paper towel to dry.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cut crusts from bread; place in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place slices of cheese on top of each slice of bread.
Mix eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt in medium bowl.
Pour this mixture over cheese and bread.
Melt 1/4 cup oleo and drizzle over mixture.
Cover with foil overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until light brown.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon extract.
Add 3 cups flour that has been sifted with baking powder and salt; blend well.
Add 1 cup flour to pecans and raisins; mix into batter.
Mix well.
Put into 9 or 10-inch tube cake pan that has been greased well and dusted with flour.
Bake in a 275° oven for 2 hours.
Let cool in pan for about 7 or 8 minutes; turn out.
Cool and store like fruit cake.
Better after a day or two.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Trim off cabbage leaves.
Mix all other ingredients together. Divide mixture into 10 to 12 portions.
Wrap each ball in a leaf and fasten with a toothpick.
Brown cabbage rolls in Wesson oil. Pour off fat.
Cover rolls with tomato sauce.
Cook slowly, covered, for about 40 minutes; stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry cream delight cake
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool at room temperature.

title: alison's shrimp and pasta salad
directions: Fix whole bag of pasta.
Cool in the refrigerator.
Boil shrimp; shell shrimp and devein.
Cut each shrimp into thirds. Cool in the refrigerator.
Boil eggs.
Cool in the refrigerator.

title: spinach salad
directions: To make dressing, mix oil, sugar, catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Put in refrigerator.
Fry bacon crisp.
Drain chestnuts and sprouts well.
Mix all ingredients and enjoy!!
Put as much dressing on salad as you like.

title: english tuna melt
directions: Split and toast English muffins, butter one-half lightly and place 1 slice of cheese on the other half.
Put tuna on the buttered half.
Place sliced avocado and alfalfa sprouts on top of tuna.
Close the sandwich and bake at 400° just until cheese melts.

title: peanut roast
directions: Mash beans and rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour.
The top should be just like a cake.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring water, sugar, syrup and salt quickly to a soft boil, then add peanuts.
Stir and cook to crack stage and take off fire. Add soda and stir until all is mixed and pour it out.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: joy's pasta with chicken and broccoli
directions: In a large skillet, heat the oil.
Saute garlic 1 minute until golden, stirring constantly. Add chicken strips and saute until white, about 7 to 10 minutes. Add broccoli and saute until crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes, basil, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper. Add wine, chicken broth and butter.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Toss pasta with chicken mixture. Serve with grated cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces, combine with green onions and green pepper, chill.
Prepare and chill tomatoes, cheese and olives.
Brown beef and chopped onion, spoon off fat.
Stir in salt, taco seasoning mix and corn.
Cool to a little warmer than lukewarm.
While meat mixture is cooling, cube avocado and toss with small amount of lemon juice.
When ready to serve, place 1/2 lettuce mixture in large salad bowl; layer with 1/2 the corn chips and remaining meat mixture.
Top with 1/2 each of the tomatoes, cheese, olives and avocado.
Repeat with remaining salad ingredients.
Drizzle taco sauce over salad and serve with additional taco sauce if desired.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn in large well-greased broiler pan.
In a heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour syrup over corn, mixing well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
When cool, separate kernels.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: curried pork chops
directions: Coat chops with flour; set aside remaining flour.
Brown chops on both sides in fat in an ovenproof frypan.
Remove pan from heat. Remove excess fat.
Cover chops with mushrooms.

title: herbal sun tea
directions: Put tea bags into a clear gallon container.
Bruise the herbs by crushing in your hands and add.
Fill the container with water and set in the sun for at least 4 hours.
Remove tea bags and herbs.
Sweeten to taste.

title: barley casserole
directions: Heat margarine in saucepan; add barley and onion and saute only until a light golden color.
Add almonds, dry onion soup and chicken broth.
Saute mushrooms a few minutes in a little margarine and add to barley along with water chestnuts and liquid drained from canned mushrooms.
Stir well, turn into casserole, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, adding more liquid if necessary.
(A little more chicken broth may be used if required.)

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and follow the directions of Solomon for bringing up a child; Proverbs 23:14 (that is "beat him with a rod").
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes; cool.

title: bootlegger beans
directions: Saute bacon.
To bacon drippings, add chopped onion and saute. Crumble bacon.
Add bacon and onion to pork and beans.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix the cooked rice
with
all
other ingredients.
Mix salad dressing with vinegar,
sugar, mustard, salt and pepper. Mix all together.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Mix flour, egg and milk; beat until well blended (but do not overbeat, or pancakes will be tough).
Let sit a few minutes. Drop by large spoonfuls onto hot griddle; you'll know when to turn them over.
The edges will have a few bubbles, then flip over and cook a few seconds.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns and 1/2 stick margarine together.
Set aside. Mix sour cream, soup, onion, Cheddar, salt and pepper together. Mix this mixture with the potatoes.
Sprinkle top with crumbs. Melt rest of the margarine and pour over top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Also good reheated.

title: southern ambrosia apple pie
directions: Line pastry shell with foil. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes. Remove from oven; remove foil. Cool. In a saucepan over medium heat, bring brown sugar, apple juice, butter, cornstarch and salt to a boil. Stir in apples and lemon juice; cook and stir over low heat until apples are crisp tender, 5-8 minutes. Pour into pastry shell. In a small bowl, beat egg, milk, sugar, coconut, vanilla and cinnamon; mix well. Pour over apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until set. Cool on a wire rack. For topping, beat cream cheese and sugar in a mixing bowl. Stir in pecans and vanilla. Fold in whipped topping. Spread over pie. Garnish with pecans if desired. Chill for 4-6 hours.

title: captain's punch
directions: Combine lemonade and orange juice concentrates, sugar, bitters and rum.
Mix well.
Place a large block of ice in large punch bowl.
Pour punch mixture over ice.
Add carbonated water.
Stir well.
Garnish with lemon and orange slices.
Makes about 24 (4 ounce) servings.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown. Mix oleo and garlic and brush over warm biscuits.

title: old-fashioned biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter or shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With fork, stir in buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead about 10 times to form a smooth ball.
Do not overknead or biscuits will not be tender. Roll out to a 6 x 6-inch square.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. With knife, cut dough into 12 portions; don't separate.
Leave biscuits in squares.
Bake at 400° until golden, about 15 minutes.

title: carrot-pineapple cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Prepare cake pans by lightly greasing with Crisco shortening (not oil). Cut waxed paper to fit bottom of pans (if using layer cake pans). Put paper in pans; press and turn, then turn over.
Flour lightly. Pour batter into pans.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
If using oblong 9 x 13-inch pan, do not line with wax paper.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and mash or beat with mixer.
Add all other ingredients.
Beat together.
Put in oblong baking dish or pan about 14 x 8 x 2-inch deep.

title: crisp coconut oaties
directions: Cream butter with sugars.
When the mixture is light and fluffy, stir in egg, vanilla and coconut flavor; beat well and set aside.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and soda. Stir this mixture into butter-sugar mixture.
Blend well, then stir in coconut, oats and Rice Krispies.
Roll into 1 or 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes, or until the cookies are golden brown.

title: egg bread braid
directions: In a mixer bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt. Mix well.
In saucepan, heat water, milk and shortening until warm.
Add to flour mixture. Add eggs, blending at low speed, then beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Add flour to make a firm dough. Knead on floured surface until elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn to grease top. Cover and let rise 1 hour.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Blend in Egg Beaters, vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Best if eaten within 24 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Pinch cake into bite size pieces.
Mix sugar, sour cream, Cool Whip, and milk.
Mix together.
Pour over cake and mix well. Mix strawberries and pie glaze.
Pour over top of cake in a punch bowl.
Let stand in refrigerator over night.

title: perfect pie crust(makes 2)
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt mixture with a fork or pastry blender until crumbs are coarse and granular.
Add cold water, a little at a time.
Mix quickly and evenly through the flour until the dough just holds together.
Roll half the dough to about one-eighth inch thickness.
Lift edge of pastry cloth and roll crust onto rolling pin.
Line pie pan, allowing 1/2-inch crust to extend over edge.
Add filling.
Roll out top crust, making several gashes to allow escape of steam.
Place over filling allowing top crust to overlap lower crust.
Fold top crust under the lower and crimp edges.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: mad hatter meatballs
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender. Stir in rice soup, tomato soup and water.
Heat to boiling.
Turn down heat and simmer sauce, stirring occasionally.
While sauce cooks, make meatballs.
Beat egg slightly in bowl.
Add and mix ground beef, bread, milk and salt.
Shape into balls about the size of ping-pong balls.
Drop balls into simmering sauce and cook slowly about 1 hour or until sauce has thickened.

title: evan's summer refresher
directions: Squeeze together in 1/2-gallon pitcher oranges, lemons and lime.
Add water to top off pitcher.
Sugar to taste.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour and shortening until mealy.
Start adding buttermilk, a little at a time, until well blended.
Pour dough onto a piece of wax paper sprinkled with flour.
Knead dough; roll out or flatten with hands.
Cut out biscuits and bake in a 425° until brown.

title: mapleine pancake syrup
directions: Mix all together and heat to boiling. Can be served hot or cold on pancakes.

title: play dough
directions: Add your food coloring to the water.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl and add colored water, a little at a time, until it feels like dough.
It may be a little oily, so play with it on a sheet of newspaper.
Store in a plastic bag or airtight container and store in the fridge.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake(first prize winner)
directions: Blend all ingredients together, except brown sugar and nuts, in large mixer bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Do not underbake.
Cool 15 minutes in pan. Spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cinnamon-apple coffee cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg and add to 1/2 cup milk.
Cut oil into dry mixture.
Reserve two tablespoons of this mixture and add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir only until moistened. Spread batter into an oiled 8-inch baking pan.
Arrange apple slices on top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased pie pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: orange cream slush
directions: Pour orange juice into 2-quart freezer container. Cover and freeze for 2 1/2 hours or until slushy, stirring twice.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In medium pot, cook sugars, syrup and water until soft ball stage (10 to 15 minutes).
Stir constantly. Stir in butter, pecans and vanilla. Beat about 2 minutes.
Drop by tablespoons on well-buttered waxed paper.
Chill until completely cold.

title: angel food strawberry cake delight
directions: Tear angel food cake in pieces and lay flat in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In mixer, mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and Cool Whip. Spread on top of cake evenly.
Cut up fresh strawberries and place on cream cheese mixture.
Place strawberry glaze on top of strawberries and refrigerate.

title: divinity candy(this is willie mae bridge's)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and salt in boiler.
Let boil until it spins a thread from spoon to boiler.
Have egg whites stiffly beaten.
Take slowly boiling syrup out by spoonful, about half and beat into egg whites.
Let other half cool slowly, a little longer (it will be harder).
Pour into mixture.
Beat until cool.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Continue to beat until creamy.
Put out by small spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: reeses cup
directions: Melt margarine and then add peanut butter and powdered sugar. Mix well.
Press into 9 x 13 pan.
